我去换衣服  很快就好
I'll dress in here.

326
00:21:35,711 --> 00:21:37,292
I shan’t be long.

327
00:21:40,090 --> 00:21:44,156
你比较喜欢哪个  纽约还是曼陀丽
Which would you prefer,New York or Menderley?

328
00:21:44,158 --> 00:21:47,389
别开玩笑了  范・霍珀太太正在等着
Oh,please don’t joke about it.

329
00:21:47,390 --> 00:21:50,611
我最好马上说再见
Mrs.Van Hopper’s waiting. I’d better say goodbye now.

330
00:21:50,623 --> 00:21:53,124
我再重复一遍
I’ll repeat what I said.

331
00:21:53,125 --> 00:21:55,731
你要跟范・霍珀太太去美国
Either you go to America with Mrs.Van Hopper,

332
00:21:55,732 --> 00:21:58,129
还是跟我一起回曼陀丽
or you come home to Manderley with me.

333
00:21:58,130 --> 00:22:00,423
你是说  你想雇一个秘书之类的人?
You mean you want a secretary or something?

334
00:22:00,528 --> 00:22:03,551
我是要你嫁给我  你这个小傻瓜
I’m asking you to marry ma,you little fool.

335
00:22:11,165 --> 00:22:13,354
请进
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

336
00:22:12,289 --> 00:22:13,495
MAXIM: Come in.

337
00:22:15,336 --> 00:22:18,359
是我的吗  我饿死了  一点早餐都没吃呢
Is that my food? I’m famished. I didn’t have any breakfast.

338
00:22:33,689 --> 00:22:37,327
你对我的建议好像不领情啊  抱歉
My suggestion didn’t seem to go at all well. Sorry.

339
00:22:37,338 --> 00:22:39,006
你不懂
Oh,but you don’t understand. It’s the...

340
00:22:39,007 --> 00:22:41,810
男人可不找我这样的人结婚
-I’m not the sort of person men marry -What on Earth do you mean?

341
00:22:41,822 --> 00:22:44,532
你这话究竟是什么意思

342
00:22:44,533 --> 00:22:46,930
至少有一点  我不是你那个圈子里的人
I don’t belong in your sort of world,for one thing.

343
00:22:46,931 --> 00:22:49,120
什么圈子
Well,what in my sort of world?

344
00:22:49,121 --> 00:22:52,144
曼陀丽啊  你知道我的意思
Well,Manderley. You know what I mean.

345
00:22:52,145 --> 00:22:54,959
你是不是属于那个圈子  只有我才能下判断
Well,I’m the best judge of whether you belong there or not.

346
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:57,357
当然  如果你不爱我  那就是另一回事了
Of course,if you don’t love me,that’s a different thing.

347
00:22:57,358 --> 00:22:59,755
这对我的自负倒是一个很好的教训
Fine blow to my conceit,that’s all.

348
00:22:59,758 --> 00:23:02,468
我爱你  非常非常爱
I do love you. I love you most dreadfully.

349
00:23:02,469 --> 00:23:06,638
我整个早上都在哭  因为我以为再也见不到你了
I’ve been crying all morning because I thought I’d never see you again.

350
00:23:09,663 --> 00:23:11,643
愿上帝保佑你
Bless you for that.

351
00:23:13,313 --> 00:23:17,587
某天我会使你想起此事  你不会相信我
If I remind you of this one day and you won't believe me.

352
00:23:18,422 --> 00:23:21,549
很遗憾你必须长大
It’s a pity you have to grow up.

353
00:23:21,550 --> 00:23:24,156
现在搞定了  你可以帮我倒杯咖啡了
Well,now that’s settled. You way pour me out some coffee.

354
00:23:24,157 --> 00:23:26,971
加两块糖跟一些牛奶  谢谢
Two lumps of sugar and some milk,please. Same with my tea,don’t forget.

355
00:23:26,973 --> 00:23:29,579
茶也一样  别忘了

356
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:31,977
谁去跟范・霍珀夫人谈这件事儿  你去还是我去
Who is going to break the news to Mrs.Van Hopper? Shall you or should I?

357
00:23:31,978 --> 00:23:34,063
你去跟她说  她一定会气个半死
You tell her.She’ll be so angry.

358
00:23:34,064 --> 00:23:36,252
她房间电话多少
What’s the number of her room?

359
00:23:36,253 --> 00:23:39,172
她不在房间  她在楼下车里
She’s not there. She’s downstairs in the car.

360
00:23:39,173 --> 00:23:41,883
喂  请帮我接前台
Hello. Give me the desk,please.

361
00:23:44,282 --> 00:23:47,931
喂  你会看到范・霍珀太太在外面车里等着
Hello.You’ll find Mrs.Van Hopper waiting outside in her car.

362
00:23:47,932 --> 00:23:50,433
你去叫她  并代我向她致意
Would you ask her,with my compliments,

363
00:23:50,435 --> 00:23:53,145
问她是否愿意来我房间
if she’d very kindly come up and see me is my room?

364
00:23:53,146 --> 00:23:55,126
是的  到我房间
Yes,is my room.

365
00:23:56,483 --> 00:23:59,506
德温特先生说请你到他房间
Mr.de Winter says please for you to come up to his room.

366
00:23:59,507 --> 00:24:03,260
德温特先生?  乐意之极
Mr. de Winter?

367
00:24:02,316 --> 00:24:03,852
Why,certainly.

368
00:24:08,474 --> 00:24:11,403
这并不是你理想中的求婚  是吗
(MAXIM CHUCKLING)

369
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:12,731
This isn’t at all your idea of a proposal.is it?

370
00:24:11,915 --> 00:24:13,582
应该在温室中
It should be is a conservatory,

371
00:24:13,948 --> 00:24:17,440
你穿着白色连衣裙  手里拿着一束红玫瑰
you in a white frock,with a red rose in your hand,

372
00:24:17,442 --> 00:24:19,735
并且在远处有人拉着小提琴
and a violin playing in the distance,

373
00:24:19,736 --> 00:24:23,281
我该站在棕树后面像你求爱
and I should be making violent love to you behind a palm tree.

374
00:24:23,282 --> 00:24:26,294
亲爱的小可怜  不用担心
Poor darling. Never mind.

375
00:24:26,306 --> 00:24:28,598
我不担心
I don’t mind.

376
00:24:28,599 --> 00:24:33,082
别担心 你无需开口
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

377
00:24:29,051 --> 00:24:31,963
Don’t worry.Don’t worry.You won’t have to say a word.

378
00:24:33,083 --> 00:24:35,376
很高兴你叫我来  德温特先生
I’m so glad you called me,Mr.de winter

379
00:24:35,377 --> 00:24:38,807
我正赶着离开  没告诉你真太不礼貌了
I was making a hasty departure.

380
00:24:38,818 --> 00:24:40,798
今早有个电报发过来说
It was so rude of me not to let you know.

381
00:24:40,799 --> 00:24:42,779
我女儿要结婚了
But a cable came this morning announcing that my daughter

382
00:24:42,886 --> 00:24:45,179
那太巧了  范・霍珀太太
in engaged to be married.

383
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:44,934
That’s rather a coincidence,Mrs.Van Hopper.

384
00:24:45,180 --> 00:24:47,785
我叫您来这儿  正是为了告诉您我订婚的事
I asked you up here in order to tell you of my engagement.

385
00:24:47,891 --> 00:24:50,799
你不会是开玩笑吧  太棒了
You don’t mean it. How perfectly wonderful.

386
00:24:50,810 --> 00:24:53,937
多么浪漫啊  谁是那位幸运的姑娘
How romantic. Who is the lucky lady?

387
00:24:53,938 --> 00:24:57,785
我为以如此唐突的方式夺走您的同伴而道歉
I apologize for depriving you of your companion in this adrupt way.

388
00:24:57,796 --> 00:25:00,715
我真希望不会为您造成太大的不便
I do hope it won’t inconvenience you too greatly.

389
00:25:00,716 --> 00:25:03,113
这些都是什么时候发生的事
When did all this happen?

390
00:25:03,114 --> 00:25:06,450
就刚才  范・霍珀太太  就在几分钟之前
Just now,Mrs.Van Hopper. Just a few minutes ago.

391
00:25:06,451 --> 00:25:09,057
我简直不敢相信
I simply can’t believe it.

392
00:25:10,831 --> 00:25:11,769
我想我应该因你没跟我
And I suppose I ought to scold you

393
00:25:11,770 --> 00:25:14,428
透露半点风声而责怪你
for not having breathed a word of all of this to me.

394
00:25:14,627 --> 00:25:15,940
我在想什么呀
What am I thinking of?

395
00:25:16,191 --> 00:25:19,276
我该恭喜祝福你们俩
I should give you both my congratulations and my blessings.

396
00:25:19,277 --> 00:25:22,811
我真替你们俩开心  什么时候在哪里举行婚礼
I’m very happy for you both.

397
00:25:22,822 --> 00:25:25,950
-在这儿  越快越好  -闪电结婚啊
-When and where is the wedding to be? -Here,as soon as possible.

398
00:25:25,951 --> 00:25:29,182
好极了  我可以推迟船期1周
A whirlwind romance. Splendid! I can easily postpone my sailing for a week.

399
00:25:29,183 --> 00:25:31,163
这可怜的孩子没有母亲
This poor child has no mother,

400
00:25:31,164 --> 00:25:33,353
所以我该承担所有安排事物的责任
so I shall take responsibility for all the arrangements.

401
00:25:33,354 --> 00:25:35,334
嫁妆  接待等等
Trousseau,reception and everythinp,and I'll give the bride away.

402
00:25:35,336 --> 00:25:37,733
并由我将新娘交给新郎  但我们的行李
But our luggage.

403
00:25:37,734 --> 00:25:40,194
下去告诉门僮把所有东西都从车里搬出来
Go down and tell the porter to take everything out of the car.

404
00:25:40,195 --> 00:25:40,861
等等
Just a minute.We’re most grateful,Mrs.Van Hopper,

405
00:25:40,862 --> 00:25:42,842
我们不胜感激  但我想我们俩

406
00:25:42,844 --> 00:25:45,554
都比较喜欢低调处理此事
but I think we’d both prefer to have it all as quiet as posaible.

407
00:25:45,555 --> 00:25:48,984
-我不能让您改船期  -但是
And I couldn't possibly allow you to change your sailing plans.

408
00:25:48,996 --> 00:25:52,540
不 亲爱的  我下去看看  把你的行李拿回来
―Oh,but... -No,no,no.

409
00:25:50,049 --> 00:25:52,256
Dear,I’ll go down and see that your luggage in brought back.

410
00:25:52,541 --> 00:25:54,729
谢谢  马克西姆
Thank you,Maxim.

411
00:25:54,730 --> 00:25:58,275
那么  这事是在我生病期间发生的
So this is what’s been happening during my illness.

412
00:25:58,380 --> 00:26:00,986
网球课  那才怪呢
Tennis lessons,my foot.

413
00:26:00,988 --> 00:26:03,593
我猜我得颁个闪电恋爱奖给你
I suppose I’ve to hand it to you for a fast worker.

414
00:26:03,594 --> 00:26:06,617
这事怎么给你办成的  静水流深啊
How did you manage it?

415
00:26:05,314 --> 00:26:07,726
Still waters certainly run deep.

416
00:26:10,581 --> 00:26:14,219
你说  你有没有做什么不该做的事情
Tell me,have you been doing anything you shouldn’t?

417
00:26:14,230 --> 00:26:17,461
我不明白你在说些什么

418
00:26:17,463 --> 00:26:18,598
好吧  没有关系
-I don’t know what you mean. -Well,never mind.

419
00:26:18,599 --> 00:26:21,622
我常说英国男人的品味很怪异
I always did say that Englishmen have strange tastes.

420
00:26:21,633 --> 00:26:24,969
你今后要担负曼陀丽女主人的职责
You certainly have your work cut out as mistress of Manderley.

421
00:26:24,970 --> 00:26:27,002
说句老实话  亲爱的  我看你根本对付不了
To be perfectly frank with you,my dear,I can’t see you doing it.

422
00:26:27,015 --> 00:26:28,411
你没有经验
You haven't the experience,

423
00:26:28,422 --> 00:26:33,718
你一点也不懂做一名好夫人意味着什么
you haven’t the faintest idea what it means to be a great lady.

424
00:26:33,730 --> 00:26:36,023
当然  你知道他为什么要娶你
Of course you knoe why he's marrying you,don’t you?

425
00:26:36,024 --> 00:26:38,421
你不会自欺欺人地以为他爱着你吧
You haven’t flattered yourself that he’s in love with you?

426
00:26:38,422 --> 00:26:41,132
实际情况是一幢空房子弄得他神经受不了
Fact is,that empty house got on his nerves to such an extent,

427
00:26:41,133 --> 00:26:43,113
简直要把他逼疯
he nearly went off his head.

428
00:26:43,114 --> 00:26:45,407
他只是无法继续独居
He just couldn’t go on living alone.

429
00:26:45,408 --> 00:26:48,952
范・霍珀太太  你该走了  你会赶不上火车的
You’d better leave,Mrs.Van Hopper.You’ll miss your train.

430
00:26:54,794 --> 00:26:57,504
德温特太太
(SCOFFS)

431
00:26:57,505 --> 00:27:00,319
再见  亲爱的  祝你好运
Mrs.de Winter

432
00:26:58,992 --> 00:27:01,449
Goodbye,my dear,and good luck!

433
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:07,914
(DOOR CLOSES)

434
00:27:19,221 --> 00:27:20,802
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

435
00:27:28,161 --> 00:27:31,799
先生  你忘了拿结婚证书
Monsieur!

436
00:27:30,190 --> 00:27:31,680
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

437
00:27:31,811 --> 00:27:35,251
他说我忘了拿我们的结婚证书
What is he saying?

438
00:27:33,443 --> 00:27:35,183
He says I’ve forgotten the proof that we’re married.

439
00:27:35,252 --> 00:27:37,232
天哪
Good heavens.

440
00:27:42,578 --> 00:27:44,534
(BOTH LAUGHING)

441
00:27:44,637 --> 00:27:47,243
有人跟我们有同样的想法呢
Somebody else had the same idea.

442
00:27:53,709 --> 00:27:56,106
-她很漂亮吧  -是的
-Isn't she sweet? -Yes.

443
00:27:56,107 --> 00:27:59,130
你喜欢穿婚纱  对吧
You’d have liked a bridal veil,wouldn’t you?

444
00:28:00,903 --> 00:28:02,884
或者至少
Or at least...

445
00:28:02,885 --> 00:28:05,490
夫人  多少钱  全要了
(BOTH SPEAKING FRENCH)

446
00:28:05,491 --> 00:28:09,338
非常感谢  夫人  谢谢

447
00:28:09,350 --> 00:28:11,956
马克西姆  好美啊
Oh,Maxim,how lovely.

448
00:28:11,957 --> 00:28:14,563
太美了
How perfectly lovely.

449
00:28:14,668 --> 00:28:18,838
太美了
(STUTTERING)

450
00:28:18,155 --> 00:28:19,645
Perfectly lovely

451
00:28:21,158 --> 00:28:22,398
(CAR HONKING)

452
00:28:24,678 --> 00:28:28,327
-欢迎回家  德温特先生  -谢谢  史密斯
SMITH:Welcome home,Mr.de Winter.MAXIM: Thank you,Smith.

453
00:28:36,358 --> 00:28:39,798
-冷吗  亲爱的  -有一点儿
-Gold,darling? -Yes,just a little bit.

454
00:28:41,467 --> 00:28:44,177
没必要害怕
There’s no need to be frightened,you know.

455
00:28:44,282 --> 00:28:47,305
你只要态度真诚自然  他们肯定都会喜欢你
Just he yourself,and they’ll all adore you?

456
00:28:51,373 --> 00:28:53,196
至于家务  你一点不用过问
You don’t have to worry about the house at all.

457
00:28:53,250 --> 00:28:57,211
丹弗斯太太是管家  交给她就行了
Mrs. Danvers is the housekeeper Just leave it to her.

458
00:29:02,009 --> 00:29:06,283
下雨了  我们最好开快点
Hello.It’s starting to rain. We’d better hurry up.

459
00:29:10,038 --> 00:29:12,957
给  披上这个  盖在你头上
Here. Have this. Put it over your head.

460
00:29:12,958 --> 00:29:15,042
谢谢
Thank you.

461
00:29:29,225 --> 00:29:32,144
到了  那就是曼陀丽
MAXIM:That’s it.That’s Manderley.

462
00:29:57,588 --> 00:29:59,568
我们到了  弗里思  大家都好吗
-Here we are. Frith everybody well? -Yes,thank you,sir.

463
00:29:59,569 --> 00:30:01,758
很好  谢谢  先生  很高兴看到您回家  先生
Glad to see you home,sir.

464
00:30:01,759 --> 00:30:04,677
-这位是德温特太太  弗里思  -你好
-This is Mrs.de Winter,Frith. -How do you do?

465
00:30:12,394 --> 00:30:15,417
我没料到会所有人都出来迎接
I didn’t expect the whole staff to be in attendance.

466
00:30:15,418 --> 00:30:17,398
丹弗斯太太嘱咐的  先生
Mrs.Danvers’orders,sir.

467
00:30:17,399 --> 00:30:20,318
抱歉  不会很久的
Oh. Sorry about this. It won’t take long.

468
00:30:29,913 --> 00:30:32,102
这位是丹弗斯太太
This is Mrs. Danvers.

469
00:30:34,188 --> 00:30:36,168
你好
How do you do?

470
00:30:37,316 --> 00:30:39,296
你好
How do you do?

471
00:30:39,297 --> 00:30:41,590
我已为您准备好一切
I have everything in readiness for you.

472
00:30:41,591 --> 00:30:44,927
谢谢你的好意  我不需要什么
That’s very good of you. I... I didn’t expect anything.

473
00:30:50,142 --> 00:30:51,288
弗里思  我们要喝点茶
-I think we’d like some tea,Frith. -Ready in the library,sir.

474
00:30:51,696 --> 00:30:53,676
在藏书室里备好了  先生

475
00:30:53,792 --> 00:30:56,711
过来  亲爱的
Come along,darling.

476
00:31:09,850 --> 00:31:12,143
马克西姆  快进来
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

477
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:12,116
Oh,Maxim,come in.

478
00:31:13,917 --> 00:31:16,836
晚上好  丹弗斯太太
Oh.

479
00:31:16,837 --> 00:31:18,817
晚上好  夫人
-Good evening,Mrs.Danvers. -Good evening madam.

480
00:31:25,804 --> 00:31:28,097
希望爱丽丝能令您满意  夫人
-I hope Alice was satisfactory,madam. -Oh,yes,thank you,perfectly.

481
00:31:28,098 --> 00:31:30,391
-满意  谢谢  很满意  -她是客厅女仆

482
00:31:30,392 --> 00:31:32,894
她会照顾你  直到你的专属女佣来了为止
She’s the parlor maid.

483
00:31:31,014 --> 00:31:32,925
She’ll have to look after you until your own maid arrives.

484
00:31:32,895 --> 00:31:35,605
但我不需要女佣  我肯定爱丽丝会做得很好
Oh,but I haven’t a maid. I’m sure Alice will do very nicely.

485
00:31:35,606 --> 00:31:38,316
恐怕那不会很久  夫人
I’m afraid that would not do for very long,madam.

486
00:31:38,318 --> 00:31:41,851
作为女主人有专属女佣是很平常的
It’s usual for ladies in your position to have a personal maid.

487
00:31:41,863 --> 00:31:45,928
我希望您喜欢这些房间的新装修  夫人
I hope you approve the new decoration of these rooms,madam?

488
00:31:45,930 --> 00:31:48,327
我不知道已经换过了呢
Oh,I didn’t know it had been changed.

489
00:31:48,328 --> 00:31:50,621
我希望没有给你们带来太多麻烦
I hope you haven't been to too much trouble.

490
00:31:50,622 --> 00:31:53,227
我只是依照德温特先生的指示办事而已
I only followed out Mr.de Winter’s instructions.

491
00:31:53,228 --> 00:31:55,521
之前是什么样子的
Well,what did it look like before?

492
00:31:55,522 --> 00:31:57,711
各种各样的帷幕  帘子等等
It had an old paper and different hangings.

493
00:31:57,712 --> 00:32:00,318
除了偶尔接待宾客  这套房间不大使用
It was never used much except for occasional visitors.

494
00:32:00,319 --> 00:32:03,133
这么说  这不是他原来的卧室
Oh. Then it wasn’t Mr.de Winter’s room originally?

495
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:05,939
是的  夫人  过去他从来没用过东厢的房间
No,madam. He’s never used the east wing before.

496
00:32:05,951 --> 00:32:09,599
当然  从这儿看不到海景
Of course,there’s no view of the sea from here.

497
00:32:09,704 --> 00:32:13,040
西翼的房间是唯一的无敌海景房

498
00:32:11,263 --> 00:32:13,595
The only good view of the sea is from the west wing.

499
00:32:13,041 --> 00:32:16,470
房间很温馨  住在这儿肯定会非常舒服
The room’s very charming,and I’m sure I’ll be comfortable.

500
00:32:16,482 --> 00:32:19,609
夫人  如果您有什么事  只要告诉我就行了
If there’s anything you want done,madam,you have only to tell me.

501
00:32:19,610 --> 00:32:21,986
你来曼陀丽好些年了吧
I suppose you’ve been at Manderley for many years,longer than anyone else.

502
00:32:21,987 --> 00:32:23,144
大概比谁待的时间都长

503
00:32:23,155 --> 00:32:26,178
不  弗里思比我来得早  老爷在世的时候  他就来了
Not so long as Frith.

504
00:32:26,179 --> 00:32:28,472
那时  德温特先生还是个孩子
He was here when the old gentleman was living,

505
00:32:28,474 --> 00:32:31,601
是这样啊  你是在那以后才来的?
when Mr.de Winter was a boy.

506
00:32:28,989 --> 00:32:31,526
Oh I see. And you didn’t come till after that?

507
00:32:31,602 --> 00:32:34,834
我来时正好是头一位德温特夫人嫁过来的时候
I came here when the first Mrs.de Winter was a bride.

508
00:32:38,797 --> 00:32:42,237
丹弗斯太太  我希望我们俩能互相了解  处好关系
Mrs.Danvers,I do hope we’ll be friends.

509
00:32:42,238 --> 00:32:43,499
你对我得有点耐心
You must be petiest with me.

510
00:32:43,500 --> 00:32:45,876
因为这样的生活对我来说完全是新的

511
00:32:45,887 --> 00:32:48,389
我一定要努力适应这儿
This sort of life is new to me and I do want to make a success of it,

512
00:32:48,390 --> 00:32:50,579
让德温特先生过得幸福
and make Mr.de Winter happy,

513
00:32:50,580 --> 00:32:53,498
我知道一切家务安排全可交给你管
so I know I can leave all the household arrangements to you.

514
00:32:53,500 --> 00:32:56,940
好的  但愿一切都能遂您的心意
Very well.I hope I shall do everything to your satisfaction,madam.

515
00:32:56,941 --> 00:32:59,443
自从德温特太太去世  都是由我来管理家务
I’ve managed the house since Mrs.de Winter’s death

516
00:32:59,444 --> 00:33:02,362
德温特先生从来没表示过不满意
and Mr.de Winter has never complained.

517
00:33:08,828 --> 00:33:11,225
我现在要下楼了
I think I’ll go downstairs now.

518
00:33:46,368 --> 00:33:48,160
通过那道门就是我告诉你的
That room in the west wing I was telling you about in there,through that door.

519
00:33:48,161 --> 00:33:50,746
西厢的房间

520
00:33:50,747 --> 00:33:53,040
现在不用了
It’s not used now.

521
00:33:53,041 --> 00:33:55,542
那是这栋房里最漂亮的房间
It’s the most beautiful room is the house,

522
00:33:55,544 --> 00:33:59,505
是唯一能穿过草坪遥看大海的房间
the only one that looks down across the lawns to the sea.

523
00:34:01,070 --> 00:34:03,363
那曾是德温特夫人的卧室
It was Mrs.de Winter’s room.

524
00:35:22,300 --> 00:35:24,906
-早上好  -早上好
-Good morning. -Good morning.

525
00:35:24,907 --> 00:35:26,991
你是德温特太太  是吗
-Yon’re Mrs.de Winter,aren't you? -Yes.

526
00:35:27,097 --> 00:35:29,181
-是的  -我叫克劳莱
My name’s Crawley.I manage the estate for Maxim.

527
00:35:29,183 --> 00:35:31,893
我为马克西姆管理财产事物

528
00:35:31,894 --> 00:35:34,291
很高兴见到你
Awfully glad to meet you.

529
00:35:34,292 --> 00:35:38,254
害怕当马克西姆不在的时候所有事都堆到一块儿了
(CRAWLEY TITTERS)

530
00:35:36,051 --> 00:35:38,633
A fearful lot of stuff piled up while Maxim was away.

531
00:35:38,255 --> 00:35:40,652
是的  我肯定会这样
Yes I’m sure there must have been. I do wish I could help with some of it.

532
00:35:40,653 --> 00:35:43,363
我真的希望能帮上什么忙

533
00:35:43,364 --> 00:35:46,074
不  弗兰克绝不允许任何人帮他
No,no. Frank never allows anybody to help him.

534
00:35:46,075 --> 00:35:48,889
他就处理像账单  房租跟税务这些鸡毛蒜皮的事
He’s like an old mother hen with his bills and rents and taxes.

535
00:35:48,890 --> 00:35:50,954
走吧  弗兰克  我们必须看一下这些评估
Come on,Frank,we must go over these estimates.

536
00:35:50,955 --> 00:35:51,809
我去拿文件
I’ll get my papers.

537
00:35:51,810 --> 00:35:54,207
你会发现那边有很丰盛的早餐
You’ll find quantities of breakfast over there.

538
00:35:54,208 --> 00:35:56,386
你必须都吃完  不然就是对厨师的不敬
But you must eat it all,or Cook will be mortally offended.

539
00:35:56,388 --> 00:35:57,440
我会尽量的  马克西姆
I’ll do my best,Maxim.

540
00:35:57,441 --> 00:35:58,775
我得跟弗兰克去个地方
I have to go over the place with Frank,

541
00:35:58,776 --> 00:36:00,673
以确保万无一失
just to make sure that he hasn't lost any of it.

542
00:36:00,674 --> 00:36:02,967
但你会好好的  对吗
You’ll be all right,won’t you? Getting acquainted with your new howe?

543
00:36:02,968 --> 00:36:05,261
开始了解你的新家了吗

544
00:36:05,262 --> 00:36:07,763
看看《纽约时报》  有一篇关于
Have a look at The Times. There’s a thrilling article

545
00:36:07,764 --> 00:36:10,161
英格兰板球问题所在的尖锐文章
on what’s the matter with English cricket.

546
00:36:10,163 --> 00:36:12,455
对了
Oh,yes...

547
00:36:12,456 --> 00:36:13,999
我姐姐比阿特丽斯跟她丈夫
My sister,Beatrice,and her husband,Giles Lacy,

548
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:15,990
贾尔斯・莱斯要来吃顿中饭
have invited themselves over for lunch.

549
00:36:16,002 --> 00:36:18,086
-今天吗  -是的
-Today? -Yes.

550
00:36:18,087 --> 00:36:21,006
我猜想大姐迫不及待要来看你
I suppose the old girl can’t wait to look you over.

551
00:36:21,008 --> 00:36:22,988
你会发现她为人很直
You’ll find her very direct.

552
00:36:22,989 --> 00:36:25,282
她如果对你没有什么好感  就会当着你的面说出来
If she doesn’t like you,she’ll probably tell you so to your face.

553
00:36:25,283 --> 00:36:28,931
别担心  亲爱的  我会及时回来保护你的
Don’t worry,darling,I’ll be back in time to protect you from her.

554
00:36:28,932 --> 00:36:31,330
-再见  亲爱的  -再见  马克西姆
-Goodbye,darling. -Goodbye,Maxim.

555
00:36:31,331 --> 00:36:33,623
-再见  -再见
-Goodbye. -Goodbye.

556
00:37:13,250 --> 00:37:16,168
-早上好  夫人  -早上好  弗里思
-Good morning,madam. -Good morning,Frith.

557
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:24,301
有什么需要我为您效劳的吗  夫人
Isn’t there anything I could get for you,madam?

558
00:37:24,302 --> 00:37:28,159
不用  谢谢  弗里思  我真的不是很饿
No,thank you,Frith. I’m really not very hungry.

559
00:37:28,265 --> 00:37:30,140
谢谢
Thank you.

560
00:37:30,246 --> 00:37:33,373
-报纸  夫人  -对的  谢谢  弗里思
-The paper,madam. -Oh,yes. Thank you,Frith.

561
00:37:37,336 --> 00:37:39,421
-夫人  -脚滑了一下
I slipped.

562
00:37:39,423 --> 00:37:42,028
谢谢  弗里思
Thank you,Frith.

563
00:37:46,096 --> 00:37:49,327
-好大呀  -是的  夫人  曼陀丽是个很大的地方
-It’s big,isn’t it? -Yes,madam,Manderley is a big place.

564
00:37:49,328 --> 00:37:51,934
过去这个曾是宴会厅
This was the banquet hall is the old days.

565
00:37:51,935 --> 00:37:55,479
这仍旧用以大庆  像是大的宴会或是舞会
It’s still used on great occasions,such as a big dinner or a ball.

566
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:59,327
是这儿的传统  一周一次
And the public is admitted here,you know,once a week.

567
00:37:59,338 --> 00:38:01,318
真好
That’s nice.

568
00:38:22,488 --> 00:38:25,093
太太  您要什么

569
00:38:25,094 --> 00:38:26,595
藏书室里通常
I beg pardon,madam.

570
00:38:26,596 --> 00:38:28,326
下午才生火
I’m afraid the fire is not usually lit in the library until the afternoon.

571
00:38:28,327 --> 00:38:30,307
此刻晨室里已生了火
But you’ll find one in the morning room.

572
00:38:30,309 --> 00:38:32,915
当然  要是您吩咐在藏书室里也生火
Of course,if you wish this fire lit now,madam...

573
00:38:32,916 --> 00:38:35,730
不必  我没有这个意思
No,Frith. I wouldn’t dream of it.

574
00:38:37,191 --> 00:38:39,588
德温特太太
Mrs.de Winter...

575
00:38:39,589 --> 00:38:42,299
过去  德温特夫人在早餐后总在那儿
I mean,the late Mrs.de Winter

576
00:38:42,300 --> 00:38:45,219
写信  打电话
always did her correspondence and telephoning in the morning room,

577
00:38:45,324 --> 00:38:47,513
谢谢  弗里思
after breakfast.

578
00:38:45,615 --> 00:38:47,230
Thank you,Frith.

579
00:38:53,561 --> 00:38:55,541
怎么了  夫人
Is anything wrong,madam?

580
00:38:55,544 --> 00:38:58,671
没有  晨室怎么走
Oh,no. Which way is the morning room?

581
00:38:58,672 --> 00:39:02,112
-那边左边那扇门  -好  谢谢
Oh,it’s that door there,on the left.

582
00:39:00,922 --> 00:39:02,253
Oh,yes,thank you.

583
00:39:50,555 --> 00:39:52,341
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

584
00:39:56,127 --> 00:39:59,567
德温特太太?  恐怕您弄错了吧
Mrs.de Winter? Oh,I’m afraid you’ve made a mistake.

585
00:39:59,568 --> 00:40:03,519
德温特太太去世已经一年多了
Mrs.de Winter’s been dead for ever a year.

586
00:40:03,530 --> 00:40:06,032
我是说
Oh,I mean...

587
00:40:07,805 --> 00:40:11,767
那是内线电话  夫人
Oh.

588
00:40:11,768 --> 00:40:15,416
可能园丁长想要请示
That was the house telephone,madam.

589
00:40:12,785 --> 00:40:15,993
Probably the head gardener wishing instruction.

590
00:40:16,878 --> 00:40:19,067
你要见我吗  丹弗斯太太
Did you want to see me,Mrs.Danvers?

591
00:40:19,068 --> 00:40:21,673
德温特先生通知我  他姐姐莱斯太太
Mr.de Winter informed me that his sister,Mrs.Lacy,and Major Lacy

592
00:40:21,674 --> 00:40:23,967
跟莱斯少校会来用午餐
are expected for luncheon.

593
00:40:23,968 --> 00:40:26,366
我想知道今天的菜单是不是合意
I’d like to know if you approve of the menu.

594
00:40:26,471 --> 00:40:29,702
挺合适的  确实好极了
Oh ,well I’m sure it’s very suitable,very nice indeed.

595
00:40:29,703 --> 00:40:32,924
请您看一下  在调味两字的边上我留出了空白
You will notice,madam,that I’ve left a blank space for the sauce.

596
00:40:32,936 --> 00:40:36,688
过去德温特夫人非常讲究调味汁
Mrs.de Winter was most particular about sauces.

597
00:40:36,689 --> 00:40:39,087
我看德温特夫人喜欢什么  你们就看着办好了
Let's have whatever you think that Mrs.de Winter would have ordered.

598
00:40:39,089 --> 00:40:41,069
谢谢  夫人
Thank you,madam.

599
00:40:41,070 --> 00:40:45,542
你的信什么时候写完  罗伯特会拿去邮局寄
When you’ve finished your letters,Robert will take them to the post.

600
00:40:45,554 --> 00:40:48,159
我的 我的信?
My... My letters?

601
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:51,392
是的  当然  谢谢  丹弗斯太太
Oh,yes,of course. Thank you,Mrs.Danvers.

602
00:41:48,744 --> 00:41:51,558
-你好  弗里思  -早上好  莱斯太太
-BEATRICE: How are you,Frith? -Good morning,Mrs.Lacy.

603
00:41:51,559 --> 00:41:55,103
-德温特先生在哪儿  -跟克劳莱先生去农场了
Where’s Mr.de Winter?

604
00:41:52,635 --> 00:41:55,172
FRICH: I believe he went down to the farm with Mr.Crawley.

605
00:41:55,104 --> 00:41:58,544
真讨厌  我们来的时候  他老是不在
BEATRICE: How tiresome of him not to be bere when we arrive,and how typical.

606
00:42:01,227 --> 00:42:02,512
(WHINING)

607
00:42:10,329 --> 00:42:13,665
我必须说  老丹弗斯把这个房子管理得挺不错
BEATRICE: I must say old Danvers keeps the house looking lovely.

608
00:42:13,666 --> 00:42:17,001
她肯定跟丽贝卡学了花艺技巧
She’s certainly learned that trick of arranging flowers from Rebecca.

609
00:42:17,002 --> 00:42:19,087
我想知道现在她有多喜欢它
GIlES: I wonder how she likes it now,

610
00:42:19,088 --> 00:42:21,485
被一个交际花不断差遣
being ordered about by an ex-chorus girl.

611
00:42:21,486 --> 00:42:23,883
你到底从哪儿得知她是以前是个交际花啊
BEATRICE: Now,where on Earth did you get the idea

612
00:42:23,885 --> 00:42:27,012
他在法国南部搭上她的  不是吗
she’s an ex-chorus girl?

613
00:42:24,542 --> 00:42:26,533
He picked her up in the South of France,didn’t he?

614
00:42:27,013 --> 00:42:31,287
-是又怎样  -我的意思是说  那就是了
What if he did?

615
00:42:28,212 --> 00:42:30,544
Well,I mean to say,there you are.

616
00:42:35,876 --> 00:42:38,586
您好  我是迈克西姆的太太
How do you do?I’m Maxim’s wife.

617
00:42:38,692 --> 00:42:39,462
你好啊
How do you do?

618
00:42:39,463 --> 00:42:42,851
你跟我猜想的完全不同
Well I must say you’re quite different from what I expected.

619
00:42:42,862 --> 00:42:46,094
别说傻话了  她跟我和你讲的完全一样
Don’t be so silly. She’s exactly what I told you she’d be.

620
00:42:46,095 --> 00:42:48,909
-觉得曼陀丽怎么样  -很漂亮  不是吗
Well,how do you like Manderley?

621
00:42:48,911 --> 00:42:50,996
跟丹弗斯太太相处得怎么样
It’s very beautiful,isn’t it?

622
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:51,561
And how do you get along with Mrs.Danvers?

623
00:42:50,997 --> 00:42:54,843
以前我从未见过像她那样的人
Well. I...

624
00:42:52,904 --> 00:42:55,236
I’ve never met anyone quite like her before.

625
00:42:54,855 --> 00:42:58,607
你是说她使你害怕?  她那副尊容可实在上不了油画
You mean,she scares you.

626
00:42:56,491 --> 00:42:58,573
She’s not exactly an oil painting,is she?

627
00:42:58,608 --> 00:43:01,517
贾尔斯  你话有点多啊  到别处去吧
Giles,you’re very much in tha way here. Go somewhere else.

628
00:43:01,528 --> 00:43:03,612
我去找迈克西姆  可以吗
Well,I'll try and find Maxim,shall I?

629
00:43:03,718 --> 00:43:05,385
贾尔斯
Giles.

630
00:43:06,846 --> 00:43:09,973
我无意说丹弗斯太太坏话
I didn’t mean to say anything against Mrs.Danvers.

631
00:43:09,974 --> 00:43:12,371
你没必要怕她
Oh,there’s no need for you to be frightened of her,

632
00:43:12,372 --> 00:43:15,395
但我应该比她好相处
but I shouldn’t have any more to do with her than you can help.

633
00:43:15,397 --> 00:43:18,420
-我们可以坐下吗  -当然  请坐
-Shall we sit down? -Yes. Yes,please.

634
00:43:18,421 --> 00:43:21,746
她起初一定会疯狂嫉妒
You see,she’s bound to be insanely jealous at first

635
00:43:21,758 --> 00:43:23,842
并且她肯定对你极度不满
and she must resent you bitterly.

636
00:43:23,843 --> 00:43:26,240
-为什么  -你不知道吗
But why should she?

637
00:43:26,241 --> 00:43:29,160
我还以为迈克西姆肯定跟你说起过
Don’t you know?

638
00:43:27,396 --> 00:43:29,933
I should have thought Maxim would have told you.

639
00:43:29,161 --> 00:43:32,079
她对丽贝卡崇拜得五体投地
She simply adored Rebecca.

640
00:43:41,570 --> 00:43:44,593
-你好  罗伯特  -很好  谢谢  夫人
-How are you,Robert? -Quite well,thank you,madam.

641
00:43:44,594 --> 00:43:47,513
-牙还疼吗  -还会疼呢  夫人
-Still having trouble with your teeth? -Unfortunately,you,madam.

642
00:43:47,514 --> 00:43:51,256
该把它们都拔掉  都拔掉  讨厌的东西  牙齿
You must have them out,all of them.

643
00:43:51,267 --> 00:43:53,352
-谢谢  夫人  -好大一盘啊
-Wretched nuisances,teeth. -Thank you,madam.

644
00:43:53,353 --> 00:43:57,001
-你会打猎吗  -不会  恐怕我连骑马都不会
What a plateful.

645
00:43:53,965 --> 00:43:54,954
Do you hunt?

646
00:43:55,133 --> 00:43:57,249
No,I don’t. I’m afraid I don’t even ride.

647
00:43:57,002 --> 00:43:59,493
一定要在这儿骑马  我们都会
Yon have to ride down here,we all do.

648
00:43:59,505 --> 00:44:02,621
你骑哪种  横座马鞍还是跨骑?
Which do you ride,sidesaddle or astride?

649
00:44:02,633 --> 00:44:04,707
对了  我忘了  你不会骑马
Well,of course,I forgot. You don’t,do you?

650
00:44:04,718 --> 00:44:06,406
你一定得学啊  这儿没什么事可做
You must. Nothing else to do around here.

