Wasn’t she afraid to go out like that alone?

816
00:53:18,211 --> 00:53:20,713
她什么都不怕
She wasn’t afraid of anything.

817
00:53:24,051 --> 00:53:26,343
他们在哪儿找到她的
Where did they find her?

818
00:53:28,013 --> 00:53:32,902
大概2个月之后  大约在离海峡40英里的埃奇库姆附近
Near Edgecombe,

819
00:53:29,331 --> 00:53:32,118
about 40 miles up channel about two months afterwards.

820
00:53:32,914 --> 00:53:37,699
迈克西姆去认尸  那对他来说太可怕了
Maxim went up to identify her.

821
00:53:35,796 --> 00:53:37,707
It was horrible for him.

822
00:53:37,711 --> 00:53:40,108
是  肯定
Yes,it must have been.

823
00:53:44,176 --> 00:53:47,094
克劳莱先生  请别对我的好奇心见怪
Mr.Crawley,please don’t think me morbidly curious. It isn’t that.It’s...

824
00:53:47,095 --> 00:53:51,161
不是那样的  只是我感到有点处于劣势
It’s just that I feel at such a disadvantage.

825
00:53:51,162 --> 00:53:53,142
一直以来  不管什么时候我见到任何人
All the time,whenever I meet anyone,Maxim’s sister or even the servants,

826
00:53:53,247 --> 00:53:55,332
迈克西姆的姐姐  甚至是佣人

827
00:53:55,333 --> 00:53:58,043
我知道他们都在想同一件事
I know they’re all thinking the same thing,

828
00:53:58,044 --> 00:54:00,754
他们一直拿我跟丽贝卡比较
that they’re all comparing me with her with Rebecca.

829
00:54:00,755 --> 00:54:02,735
你不该那么想
You mustn’t think that.

830
00:54:02,737 --> 00:54:05,447
你跟迈克西姆结婚  我说不上来心里有多高兴
I can’t tell you how glad I am that you married Maxim.

831
00:54:05,448 --> 00:54:07,845
他的生活因此而整个变了样
It’s going to make all the difference to his life.

832
00:54:07,846 --> 00:54:10,556
依我所见  怎么说呢
From my point of view,it’s very refreshing

833
00:54:10,557 --> 00:54:13,580
找到一个像你这样完全曼陀丽
to find someone like yourself,

834
00:54:11,623 --> 00:54:14,911
who’s not entirely in tune,shall we say,with Manderley.

835
00:54:13,581 --> 00:54:15,979
不搭的人  非常新鲜

836
00:54:15,980 --> 00:54:20,035
你真好  我敢说我曾犯傻过
That’s very sweet of you.

837
00:54:17,921 --> 00:54:20,412
I daresay I’ve been stupid,

838
00:54:20,046 --> 00:54:25,248
我每时每刻总意识到
but every day I realize the things she had that I lack.

839
00:54:25,260 --> 00:54:28,804
美丽  风趣与智慧
Beauty and wit and intelligence,

840
00:54:28,806 --> 00:54:32,652
还有  所有那些东西对一个女人来说都很重要
and all the things that are so important in a woman.

841
00:54:32,664 --> 00:54:35,061
但你有的那些重要的品质
You have qualities that are just as important,

842
00:54:35,062 --> 00:54:37,355
要我说的话  那更重要
more important,if I may say so.

843
00:54:37,356 --> 00:54:39,753
心地善良  待人诚挚
Kindliness and sincerity,

844
00:54:39,754 --> 00:54:42,986
还有  如果你不见怪  谦逊端庄
and if you’ll forgive me,modesty,

845
00:54:42,987 --> 00:54:44,383
对于一个做丈夫的
mean more to a husband than all the wit and beauty in the world.

846
00:54:44,384 --> 00:54:46,635
比之世界上所有的机智和美貌更重要

847
00:54:46,636 --> 00:54:51,213
任何人都不想活在过去里  尤其是迈克西姆
We,none of us want to live in the past,

848
00:54:49,036 --> 00:54:50,776
Maxim least of all.

849
00:54:51,224 --> 00:54:54,966
能否引着大家从往昔的羁缚中挣脱出来  全靠你了
It’s up to you,you know,to lead us away frow it.

850
00:54:54,979 --> 00:54:59,243
我保证我再也不会提这事了
Right.

851
00:54:56,627 --> 00:54:59,334
I promise you I won’t bring this up again,

852
00:54:59,254 --> 00:55:02,277
可在结束谈话之前
but before we end this conversation,

853
00:55:02,278 --> 00:55:05,092
你能不能如实回答我一个问题
would you answer just one more question?

854
00:55:05,093 --> 00:55:10,087
如果我知道  我会尽量回答的
If it's something I’m able to answer,I’ll do my best.

855
00:55:10,098 --> 00:55:14,164
告诉我  丽贝卡到底长什么样
Tell we,what was Rebecca really like?

856
00:55:23,237 --> 00:55:25,426
我猜想
I suppose...

857
00:55:25,531 --> 00:55:30,223
依我说  她是我有生以来见过的最美的女人
I suppose she was the most beautiful creature I ever saw.

858
00:56:02,444 --> 00:56:04,529
-晚上好  迈克西姆 -好
Good evening,Maxim.

859
00:56:04,530 --> 00:56:07,344
蜜月旅行的片子终于送到了
Hello. The films of the honeymoon have arrived at last.

860
00:56:07,345 --> 00:56:09,847
你觉得晚餐之前我们能看看吗
Do we have time,do you think,before dinner?

861
00:56:12,768 --> 00:56:14,957
你到底对自己做了些什么啊
What on Earth have you done to yourself?

862
00:56:14,958 --> 00:56:18,002
没什么  只是从伦敦订了件新衣服
Oh,nothing. I just ordered a new dress frow London.

863
00:56:18,003 --> 00:56:19,441
我希望你不会介意
I hope you don’t mind.

864
00:56:19,442 --> 00:56:23,601
不  只是你觉得那样的东西适合你吗
Oh,no,no. Only,do you think that sort of thing’s right for you?

865
00:56:23,612 --> 00:56:26,948
-它看来完全不适合你  -我以为你会喜欢的
-It doesn’t seem your type at all. -I thought you’d like it.

866
00:56:26,949 --> 00:56:30,076
还有你对你的头发做什么了
And what have you done to your hair?

867
00:56:30,077 --> 00:56:32,266
我明白了
Oh,I see.

868
00:56:32,371 --> 00:56:34,768
亲爱的  亲爱的  对不起
Dear,oh,dear.I’m sorry.

869
00:56:34,769 --> 00:56:36,854
你看起来可爱极了
You look lovely,lovely.

870
00:56:36,856 --> 00:56:39,879
改变一下也很好
It’s very nice,for a change.

871
00:56:41,757 --> 00:56:43,737
我们可以看照片了吗
-Shall we see these pictures? -Yes. I'd love to see them.

872
00:56:43,842 --> 00:56:46,239
好  我很想看

873
00:56:53,331 --> 00:56:56,041
快看  看那张
Look now,look at that.

874
00:56:56,042 --> 00:56:59,367
很棒吧  亲爱的  将来我们还能再回到那儿吗
MRS.De WINTER:Wasn’t it wonderful,darling?

875
00:56:57,789 --> 00:56:58,824
Can’t we go back there someday?

876
00:56:59,378 --> 00:57:02,297
当然可以 瞧你  那儿
MAXIM:Yes,of course. Of course. Look at you.

877
00:57:02,299 --> 00:57:05,947
当我们的子孙看到你如此可爱会非常开心的
Won’t our grandchildren be delighted when they see how lovely you were?

878
00:57:06,053 --> 00:57:08,450
瞧你
MRS.DE WINTER:Oh,look at you.

879
00:57:06,256 --> 00:57:07,871
(MAXIM LAUGHING)

880
00:57:08,451 --> 00:57:10,848
我喜欢那张
MRS.DE WINTER:Oh,I like that.

881
00:57:10,849 --> 00:57:12,829
看那张
Look at that.

882
00:57:12,830 --> 00:57:15,540
-是啊  很漂亮  -记得那张吗
MAXIM: Yes,very nice.

883
00:57:15,541 --> 00:57:18,867
-记得  -迈克西姆  我希望我们能永远度蜜月
-Remember that? -MAXIM:Yes.

884
00:57:15,891 --> 00:57:18,132
I wish our honeymoon could have lasted forever,Maxim.

885
00:57:18,878 --> 00:57:23,037
糟糕  见鬼了  等等
Dash it,look.

886
00:57:21,438 --> 00:57:22,769
Hang it.

887
00:57:23,049 --> 00:57:26,385
我又跟以前一样接错线了
I’ve threaded it up wrong as usual or something.

888
00:57:29,306 --> 00:57:31,286
弗里思  什么事
Yes,Frith. What is it?

889
00:57:31,287 --> 00:57:34,310
打扰一下  先生  我可以跟您谈件事吗
Excuse me,sir. May I have a word with you?

890
00:57:34,311 --> 00:57:37,126
好  说吧
Yes. Come in.

891
00:57:37,231 --> 00:57:39,211
事关于罗伯特的事  先生
It’s about Robert,sir

892
00:57:39,212 --> 00:57:42,548
他和丹弗斯太太之间闹了点别扭
There’s been a slight unpleasantness between him and Mrs.Danvers.

893
00:57:42,549 --> 00:57:44,633
-天哪  -罗伯特心里很不好受
Oh. dear.

894
00:57:42,542 --> 00:57:44,749
-Robert is very upset. -This is trouble.

895
00:57:44,738 --> 00:57:47,031
真麻烦  什么事
What is it?

896
00:57:47,032 --> 00:57:49,325
丹弗斯太太职责罗伯特
It appears that Mrs.Danvers has accused Robert of stealing a valuable ornament

897
00:57:49,326 --> 00:57:51,828
私藏了晨室里一件值钱的摆设
from the morning room.

898
00:57:51,829 --> 00:57:55,154
罗伯特矢口否认干过这样的事
Robert denies the accusation most emphatically,sir.

899
00:57:55,166 --> 00:57:58,294
-究竟是哪件小摆设  -是那尊爱神瓷塑  先生
-What was the thing,anyway? -China cupid,sir.

900
00:57:58,295 --> 00:58:01,317
天哪  那可是我们家的意见宝贝  是吗
Oh,dear.That’s one of our treasures,isn’t it?

901
00:58:01,318 --> 00:58:01,839
告诉丹弗斯太太
Well,tell Mrs. Danvers to get to the bottom of it somehow.

902
00:58:01,840 --> 00:58:04,654
想方设法弄清事实  我肯定不是罗伯特干的
-Tell her I’m sure it wasn’t Robert. -Very good,sir.

903
00:58:04,655 --> 00:58:06,635
太好了  先生
Why do they come to me with these things?That’s your job,sweetheart.

904
00:58:06,636 --> 00:58:10,076
他们干吗连这种事都来找我  这种事该由你管  亲爱的

905
00:58:10,077 --> 00:58:13,204
迈克西姆  我早想告诉你  可是 可是我却忘了
Maxim,I wanted to tell you,but I forgot.

906
00:58:14,874 --> 00:58:19,148
-其实是我打碎了爱神瓷塑  -你打碎的?
The fact is,I broke the china cupid.

907
00:58:17,494 --> 00:58:18,404
You broke it?

908
00:58:19,149 --> 00:58:22,370
当你刚才在弗里思面前干吗不这么说呢
Now,why on Earth didn’t you say something about it when Frith was here?

909
00:58:22,382 --> 00:58:24,362
我也不知道  我不想这么做
I don’t know. I didn’t like to.

910
00:58:24,363 --> 00:58:26,343
我怕他会拿我当傻瓜看
I was afraid he’d think me a fool.

911
00:58:26,449 --> 00:58:28,533
这下子他才真会拿你当大傻瓜看呢
He’ll think you much more of a fool now.

912
00:58:28,534 --> 00:58:31,036
现在你可得把事情向他和丹弗斯太太讲清楚
You’ll have to explain to him and Mrs.Danvers.

913
00:58:31,037 --> 00:58:33,955
-不  你去解释  我上楼去  -别像个小傻瓜似的
Oh,no,Maxim. You do it.I’ll go upstairs.

914
00:58:31,633 --> 00:58:32,839
Don’t be such a littla idiot,darling.

915
00:58:33,956 --> 00:58:36,656
大家会认为你怕他们
Anybody would think you were afraid of them.

916
00:58:36,667 --> 00:58:38,647
完全是一场误会  丹弗斯太太
MAXIM:It’s all a mistake,Mrs.Danvers.

917
00:58:38,753 --> 00:58:40,733
看来是德温特太太自己把瓷塑打碎了
Apparently,Mrs.be Winter broke the cupid herself

918
00:58:40,734 --> 00:58:42,714
后来压根把这事给忘了
end forgot to say anything about it.

919
00:58:42,819 --> 00:58:46,666
非常抱歉  没想到给罗伯特惹了麻烦
I’m so sorry. I never thought that I’d get Robert into trouble.

920
00:58:46,678 --> 00:58:49,284
那摆设还能修补一下吗  夫人
Is it possible to repair the ornament,madam?

921
00:58:49,285 --> 00:58:52,829
怕不行了　已经摔得粉碎
No,I’m afraid it isn’t. It smashed into pieces.

922
00:58:52,830 --> 00:58:55,228
你怎么处理那些碎片的
What did you do with the pieces?

923
00:58:56,897 --> 00:59:01,265
我把它们放进写字桌的抽屉里面了
Well,I put them at the back of one of the drawers in the writing desk.

924
00:59:01,276 --> 00:59:03,986
瞧德温特夫人那模样
Well,it looks as though Mrs.de Winter was afraid

925
00:59:03,987 --> 00:59:06,489
好像你会把她送进监牢似的  丹弗斯太太  对不
you were going to put her in prison,doesn’t it,Mrs. Danvers?

926
00:59:06,490 --> 00:59:07,365
找出那些碎片
Well,never mind. Do what you can to find the pieces.

927
00:59:07,366 --> 00:59:10,858
看看能否修好  并且告诉罗伯特擦干眼泪
See if they can be mended,and above all,tell Robert to dry his tears.

928
00:59:10,869 --> 00:59:13,058
我当然要向罗伯特赔个不是
I shall apologize to Robert,of course. Perhaps if such a thing happens again,

929
00:59:13,164 --> 00:59:15,040
要是以后再发生这样的事
Mrs.de Winter will tell me personally.

930
00:59:15,041 --> 00:59:16,594
德温特夫人是不是可以亲口向我讲明
MAXIM:Yes,yes,all right. Thank you,Mrs.Danvers.

931
00:59:16,605 --> 00:59:19,315
好了  谢谢  丹弗斯太太

932
00:59:23,800 --> 00:59:27,344
我猜想片段都会完好  我也不知道
Well,I suppose that clip will hold all right. I don’t know.

933
00:59:32,037 --> 00:59:35,571
亲爱的  太抱歉了  我真是粗心大意
MRS.DE WINTER:I’m awfully sorry darling.It was very careless of me.

934
00:59:35,583 --> 00:59:37,980
丹弗斯太太肯定要对我大发雷霆
-Mrs.Danvers must be furious with me. -Hang Mrs.Danvers.

935
00:59:37,982 --> 00:59:41,005
别管丹弗斯太太  你到底干吗要怕她啊
Why on Earth should you be frightened of her?

936
00:59:41,006 --> 00:59:43,403
你的举动哪像个女主人
You behave more like an upstairs maid or something,

937
00:59:43,404 --> 00:59:45,488
倒像家里的丫头呢
-not the mistress of the house at all. -Yes. I know I do.

938
00:59:45,489 --> 00:59:49,242
我知道  但我感到很不自在

939
00:59:47,167 --> 00:59:49,203
But I feel so uncomfortable.

940
00:59:49,243 --> 00:59:52,985
每天我都竭尽全力  但上上下下的人打量着我
I try my best every day,but it’s very difficult with people looking me

941
00:59:52,997 --> 00:59:57,062
就像我是一头得奖的良种母牛
up and down as if I were a prize cow.

942
00:59:57,063 --> 00:59:59,148
就算这样  那又何妨
What does it matter if they do? You must remember

943
00:59:59,149 --> 01:00:01,129
你必须记住  唯有曼陀丽发生的事
that life at Manderley is the only thing that interests anybody down here.

944
01:00:01,130 --> 01:00:03,110
才能引起人们的兴趣

945
01:00:03,112 --> 01:00:05,822
那我一定使他们大失所望了
What a slap in the aye I must have been to them,then.

946
01:00:05,823 --> 01:00:08,637
你大概是因为这个缘故才跟我结婚的吧
I suppose that’s why you married me,

947
01:00:08,638 --> 01:00:11,661
你知道我这个人呆板无趣  不爱讲话  又没见过世面
because you knew I was dull and gauche and inexperienced,

948
01:00:11,662 --> 01:00:15,092
所以这儿的人就不屑对我蜚短流长了
and there’d never be any gossip about me.

949
01:00:15,103 --> 01:00:17,500
蜚短流长?  你这话时什么意思
Gossip?What do you mean?

950
01:00:17,502 --> 01:00:20,733
我 我也不知道  我这话没别的意思
I don’t know. I just said it for something to say.

951
01:00:20,734 --> 01:00:23,235
你干吗要折服模样
Don’t look at me like that. Maxim.

952
01:00:23,236 --> 01:00:27,198
迈克西姆  怎么了  我说什么了

953
01:00:24,830 --> 01:00:27,367
What’s the matter? What have I said?

954
01:00:33,977 --> 01:00:36,677
说这些话  可不怎么悦耳动听  是吗
Wasn’t a very attractive thing to say,was it?

955
01:00:36,688 --> 01:00:40,024
是的  既唐突  又叫人讨厌
No.It was rude,hateful.

956
01:00:45,030 --> 01:00:47,844
我怀疑自己娶你  是不是干了件极其自私的事
I wonder if I did a very selfish thing in marrying you.

957
01:00:47,845 --> 01:00:49,930
你这话是什么意思
How do you mean?

958
01:00:49,931 --> 01:00:53,058
我对你可不是个好伴侣  是吗
I’m not much of a companion to you,am I?

959
01:00:53,059 --> 01:00:56,395
你并没有得到很多乐趣  是吗
You don’t get much fun,do you?

960
01:00:56,397 --> 01:01:00,566
你应该嫁给一个跟你年龄相仿的小伙子
You ought to have married a boy,someone of your own age.

961
01:01:00,567 --> 01:01:04,310
麦克斯曼  你干吗这么讲  我们当然是终生伴侣
Maxim,why do you say this? Of course we’re companions.

962
01:01:04,321 --> 01:01:07,240
是吗  我可不敢说
Ars we? I don't know.

963
01:01:07,241 --> 01:01:10,264
我这个人恐怕很难相处
-I’m very difficult to live with. -No,you’re not difficult.

964
01:01:10,265 --> 01:01:13,173
不  一点也不难相处
You’re easy,very easy.

965
01:01:13,184 --> 01:01:16,416
我们的婚姻是美满的  是天赐良缘
Our marriage is a success,isn’t it,a great success?

966
01:01:16,417 --> 01:01:19,857
我们很快活  是吧  非常非常快活
We’re happy,aren’t we? Terribly happy?

967
01:01:27,679 --> 01:01:30,076
如果你认为我们不开心
If you don’t think we are happy,

968
01:01:30,077 --> 01:01:33,204
我并不希望你言不由衷
it would be much better if you didn’t pretend.

969
01:01:34,665 --> 01:01:36,645
我会离开的
I’ll go away.

970
01:01:39,462 --> 01:01:41,546
你为什么不回答我
Why don’t you answer me?

971
01:01:43,737 --> 01:01:48,324
叫我怎么回答你呢  连我自己也搞不清楚
How can I answer you

972
01:01:45,911 --> 01:01:48,527
when I don’t know the answer myself?

973
01:01:50,411 --> 01:01:53,642
如果你说我们是快活的  那就别再往下说了
If you say we’re happy,let’s leave it at that.

974
01:01:53,643 --> 01:01:56,771
我对幸福之事一无所知
Happiness is something I know nothing about.

975
01:02:02,611 --> 01:02:05,217
看  那张
Oh,look.There’s the one when I left the camera

976
01:02:05,218 --> 01:02:08,032
我把相机放在三脚架上的时候拍的  记得吗
running on the tripod,remember?

977
01:02:08,683 --> 01:02:10,048
(INAUDIBLE)

978
01:02:19,733 --> 01:02:23,100
鉴于庄园事务赴宴伦敦

979
01:02:23,831 --> 01:02:26,322
我会在夜晚前赶回来

980
01:02:26,563 --> 01:02:30,149
这没有我的短暂假日应该也很闲适  迈克西姆

981
01:03:01,213 --> 01:03:04,236
不好意思  夫人  有什么我能为您效劳的吗
Pardon me,madam. Is there anything I can do for you?

982
01:03:04,238 --> 01:03:07,052
没事  希尔达  非常感谢
I’m all right,Hilda. Thank you very much.

983
01:03:07,053 --> 01:03:10,076
我马上去拿三明治  夫人
I’ll bring the sandwiches immediately,madam.

984
01:03:34,478 --> 01:03:36,979
-希尔达  -是的  夫人
-Hilda. -Yes,madam?

985
01:03:36,980 --> 01:03:41,035
西厢没有人再住过了  是吗
The west wing. Nobody ever uses it anymore,do they?

986
01:03:41,047 --> 01:03:44,487
没有  夫人  自从德温特太太死后就没人住了
No,madam. Not since the death of Mrs.de Winter.

987
01:04:02,464 --> 01:04:03,954
(DOOR OPENING)

988
01:04:04,257 --> 01:04:05,713
(DOOR CLOSING)

989
01:04:06,490 --> 01:04:09,200
过来  杰克先生  否则有人会看到你的
MRS.DANVERS:Come along,Mr.Jack,or someone may see you.

990
01:04:09,201 --> 01:04:11,796
丹尼  老女妖  很高兴再次见到你
FAVELL:Well,Danny old harpy it’s been good to see you again.

991
01:04:11,808 --> 01:04:14,935
得知所有消息简直令我窒息
I’ve been simply breathless to pick up all the news.

992
01:04:14,936 --> 01:04:18,584
杰克先生  我认为您不该来这里
(BARKING)

993
01:04:15,185 --> 01:04:17,141
MRS.DANVERS: I really don’t think it’s wise for you to come here,Mr.Jack.

994
01:04:18,794 --> 01:04:21,608
-杰斯珀  过来  -胡说  就像回家一样
(SOFTLY)Jasper,come here.

995
01:04:18,396 --> 01:04:20,887
FAVELL: Oh,nonsense,nonsense. It’s just like coming back home.

996
01:04:21,610 --> 01:04:25,676
-轻一点  杰克先生  -我得小心别惊动了灰姑娘
MRS. DANVERS: Quiet,Mr.Jack.

997
01:04:22,192 --> 01:04:24,683
FAVELL:Yes.We must be careful not to shock Cinderella,mustn’t we?

998
01:04:25,677 --> 01:04:26,833
她在晨室
MRS.DANVERS: She’s in the morning room.

999
01:04:26,834 --> 01:04:29,419
如果你从花园的门离开  她不会看到你的
If you leave through the garden door,she won’t see you.

1000
01:04:29,431 --> 01:04:31,723
我感觉有点像穷亲戚
FAVELL:I must say,I feel a little like the poor relation,

1001
01:04:31,724 --> 01:04:34,122
从后门偷偷离开
sneaking around through back doors.

1002
01:04:34,123 --> 01:04:38,293
-再见  丹尼  -再见  杰克先生  小心点
Well,toodle-oo,Danny

1003
01:04:35,455 --> 01:04:37,537
MRS.DANVERS: Goodbye,Mr.Jack,and please be careful.

1004
01:04:37,707 --> 01:04:38,742
(DOOR CLOSING)

1005
01:04:39,232 --> 01:04:43,298
杰斯珀  别出声
(WHINING)

1006
01:04:40,001 --> 01:04:41,616
Jasper,be quiet.

1007
01:04:44,654 --> 01:04:47,677
在找我吗  我没吓着你吧
FAVELL: Looking for me?

1008
01:04:46,091 --> 01:04:47,922
-I didn’t make you jump,did I? -No.

1009
01:04:47,679 --> 01:04:50,702
没有  当然没有  我根本不认识你
Of course not. I didn’t quite know who it was.

1010
01:04:50,807 --> 01:04:55,592
很高兴见到我吧  老伙计
Yes.You’re pleased to see me,aren’t you,old boy?

1011
01:04:55,604 --> 01:04:59,878
很高兴这个家有人欢迎我回到曼陀丽
I’m glad there’s someone in the family to welcome me back to Manderley.

1012
01:05:00,921 --> 01:05:04,361
亲爱的迈克斯老兄好吗
And how is dear old Max?

1013
01:05:04,362 --> 01:05:06,655
很好  谢谢
Very well,thank you.

1014
01:05:06,656 --> 01:05:10,399
我听说他去伦敦了  留下他的小新娘独守空闺
I hear he went up to London,left his little bride all alone.

1015
01:05:10,410 --> 01:05:12,390
这太糟糕了
It’s too bad.

1016
01:05:12,495 --> 01:05:16,457
他难道不怕会有人来把你抢走?
Isn't he rather afraid that somebody might come down and carry you off?

1017
01:05:18,127 --> 01:05:21,358
丹尼  你百般提防  结果还是枉费心机
Danny,all your precautions were in vain.

1018
01:05:21,360 --> 01:05:24,278
屋子的女主人就躲在门背后呢
The mistress of the house was hiding behind the door.

1019
01:05:26,677 --> 01:05:30,315
怎么不向新娘介绍我
Oh. What about presenting me to the bride?

1020
01:05:30,327 --> 01:05:34,288
-这位是费弗尔先生  夫人  -你好
This is Mr.Favell.madam.

1021
01:05:32,804 --> 01:05:34,294
How do you do?

1022
01:05:35,645 --> 01:05:37,625
你好
How do you do?

1023
01:05:39,295 --> 01:05:41,692
请留在这儿用茶点吧
-Won’t you have some tea or something? -Now,isn’t that a charming invitation?

1024
01:05:41,693 --> 01:05:43,882
这样盛情相邀  岂不让人心动

1025
01:05:43,883 --> 01:05:47,521
请我留下用茶点  丹尼  我还真想留下来呢
I’ve been asked to tea,Danny,and I’ve a good mind to accept.

1026
01:05:47,533 --> 01:05:49,231
也许你是对的
Oh,well,perhaps you're right. Pity,just when we were getting on so nicely.

1027
01:05:49,232 --> 01:05:51,911
可惜了  我们刚相处地很好

1028
01:05:51,912 --> 01:05:55,133
我们不可以带坏小新娘  对吧  杰斯珀
We mustn’t lead the young bride astray must me,Jasper?

1029
01:05:55,144 --> 01:05:58,584
再见  很高兴见到你
Goodbye.It’s been fun meeting you.

1030
01:05:58,585 --> 01:05:59,481
顺便说一下
Oh,and by the way,it would be very decent of you if you didn’t mention

1031
01:05:59,482 --> 01:06:01,806
要是你不在迈克斯面前提起我来过的事儿

1032
01:06:01,818 --> 01:06:05,049
那就太够朋友了
this little visit to your revered husband.

1033
01:06:05,051 --> 01:06:07,970
他对我恐怕有点看法
He doesn’t exactly approve of me.

1034
01:06:07,971 --> 01:06:11,306
-好的  -你可真够朋友
-Very well. -That’s very sporting of you.

1035
01:06:11,307 --> 01:06:15,258
我还真希望有个结婚3个月的新娘在家里等着我呢
I wish I had a young bride of three months waiting for me at home.

1036
01:06:15,270 --> 01:06:18,710
我是个孤苦伶仃的光棍
I’m just a lonely old bachelor.

1037
01:06:18,711 --> 01:06:21,108
祝你好运
Fare thee well.

1038
01:06:21,109 --> 01:06:24,121
我知道刚介绍错了
Oh,and I know what was wrong with that introduction.

1039
01:06:24,133 --> 01:06:28,615
丹尼没告诉你吧  我是丽贝卡喜爱的堂兄
Danny didn’t tell you,did she?

1040
01:06:26,316 --> 01:06:28,648
I am Rebecca’s favorite cousin.

1041
01:06:30,807 --> 01:06:32,787
再见
Toodle-oo!

1042
01:08:25,435 --> 01:08:27,096
(WINDOW SLAMMING)

1043
01:08:29,676 --> 01:08:32,389
太太  出了什么事
Do you wish anything,madam?

1044
01:08:38,446 --> 01:08:40,847
我没想到会在这儿看到你  丹弗斯太太
I didn’t expect to see you,Mrs.Danvers.

1045
01:08:40,847 --> 01:08:42,516
我看到一扇窗没关
I noticed that a window wasn’t cloned and I came up to see

1046
01:08:42,517 --> 01:08:44,813
所以我上来看看是不是能把它关严实

1047
01:08:44,814 --> 01:08:46,839
您何必对我说窗子是开着的呢
-if I could fasten it. -Why did you say that?

1048
01:08:46,839 --> 01:08:48,456
我离开屋子前就把窗关上了
I closed it before I left the room. You opened it yourself,didn’t you?

1049
01:08:48,468 --> 01:08:51,912
是您自己开的窗  对吗

1050
01:08:51,912 --> 01:08:55,241
你一直想看看这间房  不是吗  夫人
You’ve always wanted to see this room,haven’t you,madam?

1051
01:08:55,254 --> 01:08:57,967
您干吗以前不叫我领您来看呢
Why did you never ask me to show it to you?

1052
01:08:57,968 --> 01:09:00,994
我每天都准备陪您上这儿来
I was ready to show it to you every day.

1053
01:09:04,962 --> 01:09:07,363
这是个可爱的房间  是吗
It’s a lovely room,isn’t it?

1054
01:09:07,363 --> 01:09:10,076
您从来没有见过这么可爱的房间吧
Loveliest room you’ve ever seen.

1055
01:09:10,078 --> 01:09:13,209
一切都照德温特太太喜欢的摆放着
Everything is kept just as Mrs. de Winter liked it.

1056
01:09:13,209 --> 01:09:16,757
自那晚以来所有东西都没变过
Nothing has been altered since that last night.

1057
01:09:16,760 --> 01:09:19,368
来  我带您参观她的衣帽间
Come.I’ll show you her dressing room.

1058
01:09:20,727 --> 01:09:23,753
我把她所有的衣服都放在这里
Thin is where I keep all her clothes.

1059
01:09:25,320 --> 01:09:28,243
你想看  不是吗
You would like to see them,wouldn’t you?

1060
01:09:39,205 --> 01:09:41,291
感受一下
Feel this.

1061
01:09:41,397 --> 01:09:43,901
那是德温特先生送给她的圣诞礼物
It was a Christmas present from Mr.de Winter.

1062
01:09:47,138 --> 01:09:50,582
他总是送她贵重的礼物  整年都是
He was always giving her expensive gifts,the whole year round.

1063
01:09:52,671 --> 01:09:55,594
我把她的内衣放在这边
I keep her underwear on this side.

1064
01:09:57,787 --> 01:10:01,858
它们是圣克莱儿修道院的修女们专门为她做的
They were made specially for her by the nuns in the Convent of St.Claire.

1065
01:10:05,408 --> 01:10:08,644
我过去一直会等她回来  不管多晚
I always used to wait up for her no matter how late.

1066
01:10:08,644 --> 01:10:11,983
有时她跟德・维特先生直到黎明时分才回来
Sometimes she and Mr.de Winter didn’t come home until dawn.

1067
01:10:14,700 --> 01:10:18,133
她宽衣的时候  会告诉我有关她所去的派对的事
While she was undressing,she’d tell me about the party she’d been to.

1068
01:10:18,145 --> 01:10:22,529
她认识的所有相关人员  还有所有爱她的人
She knew everyone that mattered.

1069
01:10:21,426 --> 01:10:23,166
Everyone loved her.

1070
01:10:24,722 --> 01:10:27,112
当她洗好澡的时候
When she finished her bath,

1071
01:10:27,123 --> 01:10:30,879
会走进卧室  然后走向梳妆台
she’d go into the bedroom and go over to the dressing table.

1072
01:10:41,007 --> 01:10:43,408
你动过她的梳子  是吗
Oh,you’ve moved her brush,haven’t you? There.That's better.

1073
01:10:43,409 --> 01:10:46,748
在这儿  好多了  就像她一直摆放的那样

1074
01:10:46,751 --> 01:10:49,558
她会说  "快点  丹尼  梳头发"
Just as she always laid it down.

1075
01:10:47,910 --> 01:10:50,071
“Come on,Danny. Hair drill,” she would say.

1076
01:10:49,568 --> 01:10:54,568
我像这样站在她身后  每次梳20分钟
And I’d stand behind her like this and brush away for 20 minutes at a time.

1077
01:10:54,579 --> 01:10:57,188
然后她会说
And then she would say,“Good night,Danny,”

1078
01:10:57,293 --> 01:11:00,842
"晚安  丹尼"  然后她就上床休息

1079
01:11:00,590 --> 01:11:02,455
and step into her bed.

1080
01:11:09,299 --> 01:11:11,699
我亲手为她绣的这个衣套
I embroidered this case for her myself,and I keep it here always.

1081
01:11:11,701 --> 01:11:14,101
我一直把它放在这儿

1082
01:11:21,932 --> 01:11:24,958
你有见过如此精美的东西吗
Did you ever see anything so delicate?

1083
01:11:38,112 --> 01:11:41,766
瞧  你可以透过它看到我的手
Look. You can see my hand through it.

1084
01:12:03,377 --> 01:12:07,134
你不会以为她已经离开很久了吧
You wouldn’t think she’d been gone so long,would you?

1085
01:12:07,136 --> 01:12:10,047
有时我沿着这条过道走着走着
Sometimes when I walk along the corridor,

1086
01:12:10,059 --> 01:12:12,772
简直觉得她就跟在我身后
I fancy I hear her just behind me.

1087
01:12:12,772 --> 01:12:16,946
听得见她那急促而又轻快的脚步声  我绝不会搞错
That quick light step. I couldn't mistake it anywhere.

1088
01:12:16,948 --> 01:12:21,843
不仅是在这个房间  这栋房的所有房间都一样
Not only in this room,it’s in all the rooms in the house.

1089
01:12:21,855 --> 01:12:24,255
此刻我几乎也能听到
I can almost hear it now.

1090
01:12:26,136 --> 01:12:29,162
你相信死去的人会回来看活着的人吗
Do you think the dead come back and watch the living?

1091
01:12:29,163 --> 01:12:31,981
不  我不相信
No.I don’t believe it.

1092
01:12:32,086 --> 01:12:36,981
有时我真怀疑  她是不是悄悄回到了曼陀丽
Sometimes I wonder if she doesn’t come back here to Manderley,

1093
01:12:36,993 --> 01:12:40,229
注视着您和德温特先生的一举一动呢
and watch you and Mr.de Winter together.

1094
01:12:42,527 --> 01:12:47,631
你看起来很累  何不待在这儿休息一会
You look tired.

1095
01:12:45,444 --> 01:12:48,356
Why don’t you stay here a while and rest?

1096
01:12:47,642 --> 01:12:50,355
听听大海的声音?
And listen to the sea.

1097
01:12:51,713 --> 01:12:54,426
非常平静
So soothing.

1098
01:12:56,098 --> 01:12:58,080
听
Listen to it.

1099
01:13:01,527 --> 01:13:03,509
听
Listen.

1100
01:13:05,598 --> 01:13:07,790
听大海的声音
Listen to the sea.

1101
01:13:36,395 --> 01:13:39,631
告诉丹弗斯太太我要马上见她
Tell Mrs.Danvers I wish to see her immediately.

1102
01:13:51,157 --> 01:13:54,224
德温特夫妇诚邀杰克・费弗尔先生至曼陀丽庄园

1103
01:13:56,377 --> 01:13:58,402
丽贝卡  我会在那儿等你  --杰克

1104
01:14:06,462 --> 01:14:09,060
您叫我吗  夫人
You sent for me,madam?

1105
01:14:09,072 --> 01:14:11,472
是的  丹弗斯太太
Yes,Mrs.Danvers.

1106
01:14:11,473 --> 01:14:13,873
我要你把这些东西都扔掉
I want you to get rid of all these things.

1107
01:14:13,874 --> 01:14:15,961
这些是德温特太太的东西
-These are Mrs.de Winter's things. -I am Mrs.de Winter now.

1108
01:14:15,962 --> 01:14:19,302
现在我才是德温特太太

1109
01:14:19,303 --> 01:14:22,434
好  我会照您的指示做的

1110
01:14:21,415 --> 01:14:23,326
Very well.I’ll give the instructions.

1111
01:14:23,501 --> 01:14:24,991
(CAR HONKING)

1112
01:14:26,089 --> 01:14:28,802
请等一下
Just a moment,please.

1113
01:14:30,786 --> 01:14:35,055
丹弗斯太太  我不会告诉德温维特先生有关
Mrs.Danvers,I intend to say nothing to Mr.de Winter

1114
01:14:35,056 --> 01:14:36,099
费弗尔先生来访的事
about Mr.Favell’s visit.

1115
01:14:36,110 --> 01:14:40,912
事实上  我宁愿忘记一切今天下午所发生的一切
In fact,I prefer to forget everything that happened this afternoon.

1116
01:14:49,369 --> 01:14:52,082
迈克西姆  迈克西姆  一整天没看到你了
Maxim,Maxim,you’ve been gone all day.

1117
01:14:52,082 --> 01:14:55,108
你让我喘不过气来了
You’re choking me.

1118
01:14:55,110 --> 01:14:58,033
-你都做了些什么  -我在思考呢
Well,well,well,what have you been doing with yourself?

1119
01:14:58,034 --> 01:15:01,688
-思考什么  -进去我再告诉你
-I’ve been thinking. -What did you want to do that for?

1120
01:14:59,412 --> 01:15:01,448
Come in here and I’ll tell you.

1121
01:15:03,045 --> 01:15:05,759
亲爱的  我们可以举行一场化妆舞会吗
Darling,could we have a costume ball just as you used to?

1122
01:15:05,760 --> 01:15:08,682
就像以往一样

1123
01:15:08,683 --> 01:15:11,292
怎么会有这个想法
Now what put that into your mind?

1124
01:15:11,292 --> 01:15:13,274
比阿特丽斯给你洗脑了?
Has Beatrice been at you?

1125
01:15:13,276 --> 01:15:15,990
不  不是  但我感觉我们应该做些什么
No,no,but I feel that we ought to do something

1126
01:15:15,991 --> 01:15:19,748
使人们觉得曼陀丽跟以往一样
to make people feel that Manderley is just the name as it always was.

1127
01:15:21,418 --> 01:15:24,131
求你了  亲爱的  可以吗
Ok,please,darling,could we?

1128
01:15:26,533 --> 01:15:28,830
你不知道那意味着什么
You don’t know what it would mean,you know.

1129
01:15:28,831 --> 01:15:32,796
我要招待数百人  全国的人
You’d have to be hostess to hundreds of people,all the county.

1130
01:15:32,798 --> 01:15:34,488
还有很多年轻人会从伦敦赶来
And a lot of young people would come up from London,

1131
01:15:34,489 --> 01:15:36,546
会将房子变成夜总会那样
-and turn the house into a nightclub. -Oh,yes. But I want to. Please.

1132
01:15:36,556 --> 01:15:38,852
知道  但我想要嘛  求你了

1133
01:15:38,853 --> 01:15:41,879
我从未参加过大型派对  但我可以学习怎么做
I’ve never been to a large party,but I could learn what to do.

1134
01:15:41,881 --> 01:15:44,907
并且我向你保证  我不会让你丢脸的
And I promise you,you wouldn’t be ashamed of me.

1135
01:15:52,842 --> 01:15:54,929
好吧  如果你觉得你会喜欢的话
All right,if you think you’d enjoy it.

1136
01:15:54,930 --> 01:15:57,434
你最好让丹弗斯太太来帮忙  好吗
You’d better get Mrs.Danvers to help you out,won’t you?

1137
01:15:57,541 --> 01:16:00,045
不  不用  我不需要丹弗斯太太帮我
No,so.I don’t need Mrs.Danvers to help me. I can do it myself.

1138
01:16:00,045 --> 01:16:02,341
-我可以自己搞定  -好吧  我的心肝

1139
01:16:02,342 --> 01:16:05,358
谢谢  亲爱的  谢谢
All right,my sweet.

1140
01:16:03,684 --> 01:16:05,800
Thank you,darling.Thank you.

1141
01:16:05,370 --> 01:16:08,919
-你会打扮成什么  -我从不打扮

1142
01:16:08,920 --> 01:16:11,320
那是作为主人的特权
-What’ll you go as? -I never dress up.

1143
01:16:09,231 --> 01:16:11,222
That’s the one privilege I claim as the host.

1144
01:16:11,321 --> 01:16:12,405
你会打扮成什么
What will you be? Alice in Wonderland,with that ribbon around your hair?

1145
01:16:12,406 --> 01:16:14,347
漫游仙境里头发扎着缎带的爱丽丝吗

1146
01:16:14,348 --> 01:16:16,330
不告诉你  我会亲自设计我的服装
No,I won’t tell you.

1147
01:16:16,332 --> 01:16:18,419
给你一个终身难忘的惊喜
I’ll design a costume all by myself and give you the surprise of your life.

1148
01:16:34,288 --> 01:16:37,105
请进
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

1149
01:16:36,050 --> 01:16:37,256
Come in.

1150
01:16:41,283 --> 01:16:43,892
罗伯特在藏书室发现了这些画稿  夫人
Robert found these sketches in the library,madam.

1151
01:16:43,893 --> 01:16:46,606
-你打算把它们扔掉吗  -是的  丹弗斯太太
-Did you intend throwing them away? -Yes,Mrs.Danvers,I did.

1152
01:16:46,607 --> 01:16:49,623
它们只是我为舞会服装画的设计稿
They were just some ideas I was sketching for my costume for the ball.

1153
01:16:49,634 --> 01:16:51,826
德温特先生没有给你什么建议吗
Hasn’t Mr.de Winter suggested anything?

1154
01:16:51,826 --> 01:16:54,749
没有  我要给他惊喜  不想让他知道
No,I want to surprise him. I don’t want him to know anything about it.

1155
01:16:54,750 --> 01:16:57,567
我只不过想也许
I merely thought that you might find a costume

1156
01:16:57,569 --> 01:17:00,074
在家族肖像画中你会找到适合你的服装
among the family portraits that would suit you.

1157
01:17:00,075 --> 01:17:03,729
你是说挂在楼梯边上的那些画吗  我去瞧瞧
Oh,you mean those at the top of the stairs?I’ll go and look at them.

1158
01:17:11,140 --> 01:17:15,095
比如这幅  也许它是为你量身订做的
This one,for instance. Might have been designed for you.

1159
01:17:15,108 --> 01:17:17,508
我肯定你能如法炮制一件
I’m sure you could have it copied.

1160
01:17:17,508 --> 01:17:18,216
我听德温特先生讲过
I’ve heard Mr.de Winter say that this is his favorite of all the paintings.

1161
01:17:18,218 --> 01:17:21,568
这幅是所有油画里他最喜欢的一幅

1162
01:17:21,581 --> 01:17:24,712
这位是卡洛琳・德温特夫人  他的一位祖先
It’s Lady Caroline de Winter,one of his ancestors.

1163
01:17:24,712 --> 01:17:28,062
真是个好主意  丹弗斯太太
Oh,well,that’s a splendid idea,Mrs.Danvers.I’m very grateful.

1164
01:17:28,063 --> 01:17:29,618
不胜感激

1165
01:17:56,240 --> 01:17:59,476
-一切尽在掌控之中吗  弗里思  -是的  先生  谢谢
-Everything under control,Frith? -Yes,sir,thank you.

1166
01:17:59,477 --> 01:18:03,223
抱歉问一句  先生  你是要扮演一位校长吗
Excuse me,sir,are you supposed to be a schoolmaster?

1167
01:18:03,234 --> 01:18:05,738
不是  这件只是我的旧方帽长袍
Oh,no. This is just my old cap and gown.

1168
01:18:05,741 --> 01:18:09,603
无疑是件不错的服装  先生  也很节俭
It certainly makes a very nice costume,sir.And economical,too.

1169
01:18:09,603 --> 01:18:12,734
是  我就是这么想的

1170
01:18:11,353 --> 01:18:13,344
Yes. That was the idea.

1171
01:18:23,070 --> 01:18:26,096
晚上好  罗伯特  不大适合开舞会的天气
Good evening,Robet. Not very good weather for the ball.

1172
01:18:26,098 --> 01:18:29,647
-是的  先生  -路上雾很大  很冷
-No,sir. -Very misty on the way and very chilly.

1173
01:18:29,647 --> 01:18:33,499
这顶假发太紧了  应该吃片阿司匹林止疼
Oh,this wig’s so tight they ought to send an aspirin with it.

1174
01:18:33,509 --> 01:18:36,222
好啊  扮演的是什么人物  亚当跟夏娃吗
Hello.What’s the idea? Adam and Eve?

1175
01:18:36,224 --> 01:18:39,147
-马克西  别恶心人了  -是大力士  老弟
Oh. Maxim,don’t be disgusting.

1176
01:18:39,147 --> 01:18:41,339
-我的杠铃呢  -什么
-Strongman.Where’s my weight thing? -What thing?

1177
01:18:41,340 --> 01:18:43,636
-你没落在车里吧  -没有  在那儿
You haven’t left it in the car,have you?

1178
01:18:44,889 --> 01:18:47,498
你是第一个下来的吗  那丫头呢
There it is.

1179
01:18:45,346 --> 01:18:46,426
-You were the first one down? -Yes.

1180
01:18:47,499 --> 01:18:49,429
她的着装要对外保密
Where’s the child?

1181
01:18:47,723 --> 01:18:48,883
Well,she’s keeping her costume a terrific secret.

1182
01:18:49,431 --> 01:18:50,839
不让我进她的房间
Wouldn’t even let me into her room.

1183
01:18:50,944 --> 01:18:52,926
真可爱
Oh,lovely.

1184
01:18:52,927 --> 01:18:55,328
我上去帮她一把
I’ll go up and give her a hand.

1185
01:18:55,329 --> 01:18:58,146
-我可以去喝一杯  -你穿成这样不会感冒吗
-I could do with a drink. -Won’t you catch a cold in that thing?

1186
01:18:58,147 --> 01:19:01,487
别傻了  这可是纯羊毛的  老弟
Don’t be silly. Pure wool,old boy.

1187
01:19:01,488 --> 01:19:04,609
等一下  先生  您忘了拿这个
-Pardon me,sir. You forgot this. -Thank you.

1188
01:19:04,620 --> 01:19:06,707
谢谢

1189
01:19:10,571 --> 01:19:13,911
我来了  亲爱的  是小贝  我来帮你的
Here I am,dear,it’s Bea. I’ve come to give a hand.

1190
01:19:13,912 --> 01:19:17,460
请别进来  比阿特丽斯  我不想任何人看到我的装束
MRS.DE WINTER: Oh,please don’t come in,Beatrice.

1191
01:19:15,751 --> 01:19:17,412
I don’t want anyone to see my costume.

1192
01:19:17,460 --> 01:19:20,069
不会很久吧
Oh.Oh,you won’t be long,will you?

1193
01:19:20,071 --> 01:19:23,202
因为总统随时都会驾临
Because the first people will be arriving any moment.

1194
01:19:23,307 --> 01:19:25,101
你肯定是缝在那儿吗
Now,you’re sure that’s where that should be?

1195
01:19:25,102 --> 01:19:26,219
是的  夫人  肯定没错
Yes,madam,it’s just right.

1196
01:19:26,230 --> 01:19:28,631
-很激动人心吧  -的确  夫人
-Isn’t it exciting? -Indeed it is,madam.

1197
01:19:28,632 --> 01:19:30,322
我一直听说曼陀丽庄园舞会
I’ve always heard of the Manderley ball,and now I'm really going to see one.

1198
01:19:30,323 --> 01:19:31,659
现在终于可以见识一回了

1199
01:19:31,659 --> 01:19:34,268
我肯定那儿无人能与您媲美  夫人
I'm sure there will be no one there to touch you,madam.

1200
01:19:34,270 --> 01:19:37,087
你真的那么认为吗  我的扇子在哪儿
Do you really think so? Now,where’s my fan?

1201
01:19:37,087 --> 01:19:39,696
你确定我看起来很好吗
Here.

1202
01:19:38,107 --> 01:19:41,770
-You’re sure I look all right? -You look ever so beautiful.

1203
01:19:39,697 --> 01:19:42,202
您看起来漂亮极了

1204
01:19:44,082 --> 01:19:46,378
走吧
Well,here goes.

1205
01:20:37,833 --> 01:20:39,698
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

1206
01:20:47,243 --> 01:20:49,747
晚上好  德温特先生
Good evening,Mr.de Winter.

1207
01:20:55,386 --> 01:20:57,473
你知道自己干的什么好事
What the devil do you think you’re doing?

1208
01:20:57,578 --> 01:20:59,560
丽贝卡
Rebecca.

1209
01:20:59,562 --> 01:21:03,528
是那幅画  那幅画  画廊里的那副
But it’s the picture. The one in the gallery.

1210
01:21:05,930 --> 01:21:08,435
怎么了  我做了什么错事
-What is it? What have I done? -Go and take it off.

1211
01:21:08,435 --> 01:21:12,505
去  把衣服换掉  随便换什么都行  哪一件都行

1212
01:21:10,032 --> 01:21:12,614
It doesn’t matter what you put on. Anything will do.

1213
01:21:14,073 --> 01:21:17,726
你还站在那儿干吗  没听到我说的话吗
What are you standing there for? Didn’t you hear what I said?

1214
01:21:17,726 --> 01:21:20,335
布什先生跟莫里夫人到
ROBERT: Sir George and Lady Moore.

1215
01:21:20,337 --> 01:21:23,260
达德烈・泰南特上将跟玻班克夫人到
Dudley Tennant. Admiral and Lady Burbank.

1216
01:21:43,722 --> 01:21:47,376
我看着你下楼 就像一年前我看着她一样
I watched you go down,just as I watched her a year ago.

1217
01:21:47,376 --> 01:21:49,880
尽管穿着同样的衣服  但你无法与其相比
Even in the same dress,you couldn’t compare.

1218
01:21:49,881 --> 01:21:52,282
你知道的  你知道她曾穿过这件
You knew it.

1219
01:21:52,283 --> 01:21:55,100
可是你还故意建议我穿成这样
You knew that she wore it,and yet you deliberately suggested I wear it.

1220
01:21:55,100 --> 01:21:55,808
你为什么这么恨我
Why do you hate me? What have I done to you that you should ever hate me so?

1221
01:21:55,810 --> 01:21:57,907
我对你做了什么使你如此讨厌我

1222
01:21:57,920 --> 01:22:00,006
你设法取代她的位置  你让他娶你
You tried to take her place,you let him marry you.

1223
01:22:00,112 --> 01:22:02,095
我曾看着他的脸  他的眼神
I’ve seen his face,his eyes.

1224
01:22:02,096 --> 01:22:04,392
跟她去世后的前几个礼拜一样
They’re the same as those first weeks after she died.

1225
01:22:04,392 --> 01:22:07,617
我过去常常听见他整夜走来走去
I used to listen to him walking up and down,up and down,

1226
01:22:07,628 --> 01:22:09,820
一夜又一夜
all night long,night after night,

1227
01:22:10,030 --> 01:22:13,150
想起她  因失去她而遭受身心折磨
thinking of her,suffering torture because he’d lost her.

1228
01:22:13,161 --> 01:22:16,501
我不想知道  我不想知道
I don't want to know. I don’t want to know!

1229
01:22:16,503 --> 01:22:18,799
你以为你可以取代德温特太太
You thought you could be Mrs.de Winter,live in her house,walk in her steps,

1230
01:22:18,799 --> 01:22:19,873
住在她的房子里
take the thing that were hers. But she’s too strong for you.

1231
01:22:19,874 --> 01:22:22,033
走她所走过的阶梯  拿走属于她的东西

1232
01:22:22,035 --> 01:22:24,540
但她对于你来说太强大了  你无法打败她
You can’t fight her. No one ever got the better of her. Never. Never.

1233
01:22:24,541 --> 01:22:27,150
没人能胜过她  永远不会有  永远不会

1234
01:22:27,151 --> 01:22:30,166
她最终被打败  但不是被男人  或是女人所打败
She was beaten in the end,but it wasn’t a man,it wasn’t a woman.

1235
01:22:30,179 --> 01:22:34,564
-而是被大海  -别说了 别说了
It was the sea.

1236
01:22:31,447 --> 01:22:34,405
Oh,stop it. Stop it. Oh,stop it.

1237
01:22:54,189 --> 01:22:58,260
您太劳累了  夫人  我为您开扇窗户
You’re overwrought,madam. I’ve opened a window for you.

1238
01:22:58,261 --> 01:23:01,287
空气流通点  对您有好处的
A little air will do you good.

1239
01:23:14,443 --> 01:23:18,305
你干吗不走  干吗不离开曼陀丽
Why don’t you go? Why don’t you leave Manderley?

1240
01:23:18,306 --> 01:23:21,113
他不需要你
He doesn’t need you. He’s got his memories.

1241
01:23:21,124 --> 01:23:23,524
他有他的记忆

1242
01:23:23,525 --> 01:23:26,969
他不爱你  他只想跟她在一起
He doesn’t love you. He wants to be alone again with her.

1243
01:23:28,536 --> 01:23:31,354
你用不着留下
You’ve nothing to stay for.

1244
01:23:31,355 --> 01:23:35,008
你还活着干吗呢
You’ve nothing to live for,really,have you?

1245
01:23:35,008 --> 01:23:39,277
看下面  很容易  不是吗
Look down there.lt’s easy,isn’t it?

1246
01:23:39,290 --> 01:23:42,107
你为什么
Why don’t you? Why don’t you?

1247
01:23:42,108 --> 01:23:44,300
你何为什么

1248
01:23:45,762 --> 01:23:49,936
不跳下去 跳下去
Go on.

1249
01:23:50,042 --> 01:23:52,860
别害怕
Go on.

1250
01:23:50,984 --> 01:23:52,565
Don’t be afraid.

1251
01:23:58,450 --> 01:23:59,656
(EXPLOSION)

1252
01:24:01,787 --> 01:24:03,368
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

1253
01:24:03,301 --> 01:24:05,910
船只失事  是船只触礁
MAN 1: Shipwreck. MAN 2: Ship on the rocks!

1254
01:24:05,911 --> 01:24:07,893
是搁浅地的一艘船发射的烟火
-A ship aground,sending up rockets! -Shipwreck!

1255
01:24:07,894 --> 01:24:11,965
船难  大家快点  到海湾去  通知海岸巡逻队
MAN 2: Come on,everybody,down to the bay.

1256
01:24:10,087 --> 01:24:12,169
MAN 3: Notify the coast guard. MAN 4:She’s aground.

1257
01:24:11,965 --> 01:24:14,052
迈克西姆  迈克西姆
Maxim! Maxim!

1258
01:24:14,054 --> 01:24:17,487
-船靠岸了  -大家快点  快点
MAN 1: Ship ashore. MAN 2: Come on!Come on,everybody.

1259
01:24:17,499 --> 01:24:20,108
迈克西姆  迈克西姆
-MAN 2: Come on! Come on! -Maxim! Maxim!

1260
01:24:23,433 --> 01:24:25,139
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

1261
01:24:44,662 --> 01:24:45,662
噢
Oh!

1262
01:24:49,209 --> 01:24:52,002
本，你见到德温特先生了吗？
Ben,have you seen Mr.de Winter anywhere?

1263
01:24:52,337 --> 01:24:55,798
她不会回来了，是吗？你说过的
She won’t come back,will she? You said so.

1264
01:24:56,883 --> 01:24:58,967
谁？本？你说什么？
Who,Ben? What do you mean?

1265
01:24:59,636 --> 01:25:01,386
那个人
The other one.

1266
01:25:15,013 --> 01:25:16,681
弗兰克  有见过迈克西姆吗
-Frank,have you seen Maxim anywhere? -Not since about half an hour ago.

1267
01:25:16,994 --> 01:25:20,331
1个小时之前见过  我以为他去那间屋子了
I thought he’d gone up to the house.

1268
01:25:20,331 --> 01:25:22,312
没有  他根本没去过那间屋子
No,he hasn’t been in the house at all,

1269
01:25:22,312 --> 01:25:24,814
我担心他发生什么事了
and I’m afraid something might have happened to him.

1270
01:25:24,814 --> 01:25:27,630
弗兰克  怎么了  有什么不对劲吗
Frank,what’s the matter? Is anything wrong?

1271
01:25:27,630 --> 01:25:30,236
是有些事不对劲
-There is something wrong. -Well...

1272
01:25:30,236 --> 01:25:33,980
潜水员下去检查船底
The diver who went down to inspect the bottom of the ship

1273
01:25:33,990 --> 01:25:35,971
碰到另一艘船的船体
came across the hull of another boat. A little sailboat.

1274
01:25:35,971 --> 01:25:37,952
一艘小帆船

1275
01:25:39,308 --> 01:25:43,062
-弗兰克  那是   -是的  是丽贝卡的船
-Frank,is it... -Yes.

1276
01:25:41,720 --> 01:25:43,256
It’s Rebecca’s.

1277
01:25:45,460 --> 01:25:47,650
他们怎么认出它的
How did they recognize it?

1278
01:25:47,650 --> 01:25:50,559
他是个当地人  马上认出来了
He’s a local man. Knew it instantly.

1279
01:25:50,569 --> 01:25:53,593
那对可怜的迈克西姆太残忍了
It’ll be so hard on poor Maxim.

1280
01:25:53,593 --> 01:25:56,513
是的  又将所有的记忆带回来了
Yes.It’s going to bring it all back again,ask worse than before.

1281
01:25:56,513 --> 01:25:58,598
并且比之前更糟

1282
01:26:00,371 --> 01:26:02,769
他们为什么一定要找它呢
Why did they have to find it?

1283
01:26:02,769 --> 01:26:06,940
他们为什么不能让它安静地待在海底呢
Why couldn’t they have left it there in peace

1284
01:26:04,826 --> 01:26:06,782
at the bottom of the sea?

1285
01:26:08,504 --> 01:26:12,456
我最好去为那些人准备一些早餐
Well,I'd better get along and arrange some breakfast for the men.

1286
01:26:12,466 --> 01:26:15,907
好的  弗兰克  我去找迈克西姆
All right,Frank. I’ll go and look for Maxim.

1287
01:26:16,129 --> 01:26:17,994
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

1288
01:26:52,298 --> 01:26:54,487
迈克西姆
-Hello. -Maxim.

1289
01:26:54,487 --> 01:26:56,990
你整晚没睡
You haven’t had any sleep.

1290
01:26:58,762 --> 01:27:01,056
你原谅我了吗
-Have you forgiven me? -Forgiven you?

1291
01:27:01,056 --> 01:27:04,695
原谅你?  你做了什么事竟要我原谅
What have I got to forgive you for?

1292
01:27:04,706 --> 01:27:08,564
昨晚的事  有关服装的蠢事
For last night. My stupidity about the costume.

1293
01:27:08,564 --> 01:27:12,411
那个啊  我早忘了
Oh,that.

1294
01:27:12,422 --> 01:27:15,029
我对你发脾气了  是吗
I’d forgotten. I was angry with you,wasn’t I?

1295
01:27:14,646 --> 01:27:15,726
Hmm.

1296
01:27:19,304 --> 01:27:22,223
迈克西姆  难道我们不能一切从头开始
Maxim,can’t we start all over again?

1297
01:27:22,223 --> 01:27:26,384
我不奢求你爱我  我不作非分之想
I don’t ask that you should love me. I won’t ask impossible things.

1298
01:27:26,394 --> 01:27:29,105
让我做你的朋友和伙伴吧
I’ll be your friend,your companion. I’ll be happy with that.

1299
01:27:29,105 --> 01:27:31,712
那样我就很开心了

1300
01:27:37,551 --> 01:27:40,471
你很爱我  对吗
You love me very much,don’t you?

1301
01:27:44,537 --> 01:27:47,144
一切都晚了  宝贝
But it’s too late,my darling.

1302
01:27:48,604 --> 01:27:51,523
我们失去了绝无仅有的过幸福日子的机会
We’ve lost our little chance of happiness.

1303
01:27:51,523 --> 01:27:55,590
-不  迈克西姆  不  -是的  现在一切都结束了
-No,Maxim,no. -Yes.

1304
01:27:54,311 --> 01:27:55,972
It’s all over now.

1305
01:27:57,154 --> 01:27:59,657
事情终于发生了
The thing’s happened.

1306
01:27:59,657 --> 01:28:02,774
一直在我料想中的事
The thing I have dreaded day after day.

1307
01:28:02,785 --> 01:28:04,870
日复一日  夜复一夜
-Night after night. -Maxiw,what are you trying to tell me?

1308
01:28:04,974 --> 01:28:07,685
迈克西姆  你在说些什么

1309
01:28:09,145 --> 01:28:12,065
丽贝卡得胜了
Rebecca has won.

1310
01:28:13,942 --> 01:28:17,164
她的幽灵老是在你我之间徘徊
Her shadow has been between us all the time,keeping us from one another.

1311
01:28:17,174 --> 01:28:19,260
阻止我们在一起

1312
01:28:20,615 --> 01:28:23,535
她知道这事会发生
She knew that this would happen.

1313
01:28:23,535 --> 01:28:25,933
你在说什么啊
What are you saying?

1314
01:28:25,933 --> 01:28:30,406
他们派了一个潜水员下去  他找到了另一艘船
They sent a diver down.

1315
01:28:28,845 --> 01:28:31,757
-He found another boat. -Yes,I know. Frank told me.

1316
01:28:30,417 --> 01:28:33,962
我知道  弗兰克告诉我了  是丽贝卡的船

1317
01:28:32,224 --> 01:28:36,467
Rebecca’s boat. Oh,it’s terrible for you.I’m so sorry.

1318
01:28:33,962 --> 01:28:37,184
那对你来说太残酷了  对不起

1319
01:28:37,194 --> 01:28:40,009
潜水员还有另外一个发现
The diver made another discovery.

1320
01:28:40,009 --> 01:28:43,242
他弄破其中一个舱口  检查了船舱
Broke one of the ports and looked into the cabin.

1321
01:28:44,597 --> 01:28:46,891
里面有一具尸体
There was a body in there.

1322
01:28:46,891 --> 01:28:49,081
因此她并不是单独出海的
She wasn’t alone. There was someone sailing with her,

1323
01:28:49,185 --> 01:28:51,219
这说明当时她和另一个人一起出航
and you have to find out who it was,that’s it,isn’t it,Maxim?

1324
01:28:51,219 --> 01:28:52,418
你现在得查明这人是谁

1325
01:28:52,418 --> 01:28:54,503
就时这么一回事  对吗  迈克西姆
You don’t understand. There was no one with her.

1326
01:28:54,503 --> 01:28:58,768
你不明白  没人跟她一起出海

1327
01:28:58,778 --> 01:29:02,636
躺在船舱板上的是丽贝卡的尸体
It’s Rebecca’s body lying there on the cabin floor.

1328
01:29:03,992 --> 01:29:06,390
不
Oh,no.

1329
01:29:06,390 --> 01:29:09,310
被冲上埃奇库姆海岸的女人
The woman that was washed up at Edgecombe,

1330
01:29:09,310 --> 01:29:12,646
现在埋葬在家族墓地里的那个女人
the woman that is now buried in the family crypt,

1331
01:29:12,646 --> 01:29:14,940
不是丽贝卡
that was not Rebecca.

1332
01:29:15,044 --> 01:29:18,277
那是一个没人认领的无名女尸
That was the body of some unknown woman,

1333
01:29:18,277 --> 01:29:21,916
不知属于何方的女人尸体
unclaimed,belonging nowhere.

1334
01:29:21,926 --> 01:29:26,608
我认的尸  但我知道那不是丽贝卡
I identified it. But I knew it wasn’t Rebecca.

1335
01:29:26,619 --> 01:29:29,017
一切都是谎言
It wan all a lie.

1336
01:29:31,102 --> 01:29:34,126
我知道丽贝卡的尸体在哪里
I knew where Rebecca’s body was,

1337
01:29:34,126 --> 01:29:37,880
陈尸于海底的船舱板上
lying on that cabin floor on the bottom of the sea.

1338
01:29:37,880 --> 01:29:40,174
你怎么知道的  迈克西姆
How did you know,Maxim?

1339
01:29:40,174 --> 01:29:44,762
因为是我放在那儿的
Because I put it there.

1340
01:29:52,582 --> 01:29:56,127
现在你还能看着我的眼睛  告诉我你爱我吗
Will you look into my eyes and tell me that you love me now?

1341
01:30:08,640 --> 01:30:12,081
你看  我没说错
Yon see? I was right.

1342
01:30:14,062 --> 01:30:16,147
太晚了
It’s too late.

1343
01:30:21,986 --> 01:30:25,104
什么太晚了  不许再说这话
No,it’s not too late. You’re not to say that.

1344
01:30:25,115 --> 01:30:27,721
我爱你胜过世间的一切
I love you more than anything in thu world.

1345
01:30:27,826 --> 01:30:30,224
求你了  迈克西姆  吻我  求你了
-Oh,please,Maxim,kiss me,please. -No.

1346
01:30:30,224 --> 01:30:33,978
不  没用了  太迟了
It’s no use.It’s too late.

1347
01:30:33,978 --> 01:30:36,480
现在我们不能失去彼此
Oh,we can’t lose each other now. We must be together always.

1348
01:30:36,480 --> 01:30:39,598
我们必须永远在一起  没有秘密  没有阴影
No secrets,no shadows.

1349
01:30:39,608 --> 01:30:42,632
我们可能只剩几天  几个小时
We may only have a few days,a few hours.

1350
01:30:42,632 --> 01:30:44,916
迈克西姆  你之前为什么不告诉我
Maxim,why didn’t you tell me before?

1351
01:30:44,926 --> 01:30:47,950
有时我差点就讲出来了  但你那时的态度太冷漠
I nearly did sometimes,but you never seemed close enough.

1352
01:30:47,950 --> 01:30:51,693
我看出你在想念丽贝卡  还叫我怎么跟你亲热
How could we be close when I knew you were always thinking of Rebecca?

1353
01:30:51,704 --> 01:30:55,562
我看出你仍然爱着丽贝卡  怎么能要你再来爱我
How could I even ask you to love me,when I knew you Rebecca still?

1354
01:30:57,021 --> 01:31:01,714
你在胡说些什么  你这话什么意思
What are you talking about?

1355
01:31:00,246 --> 01:31:01,861
What do you mean?

1356
01:31:03,278 --> 01:31:07,751
每当你抚摸我的时候  我就想  你在拿我和丽贝卡相比
Whenever you touched me,I knew you were comparing me with Rebecca.

1357
01:31:07,761 --> 01:31:10,608
每当你对我说话  每当你看着我
Whenever you looked at we or spoke to me or walked with me in the garden,

1358
01:31:10,608 --> 01:31:12,443
或是同我一起在花园散步

1359
01:31:12,454 --> 01:31:14,539
我知道你在想
I knew you were thinking,“This I did with Rebecca,and this,and this.”

1360
01:31:14,539 --> 01:31:17,876
"我曾跟丽贝卡做过此事"

1361
01:31:17,876 --> 01:31:19,857
我说的不对吗
Oh it’s true,isn’t it?

1362
01:31:19,857 --> 01:31:23,611
你以为我爱丽贝卡?  你这么认为?
You thought I loved Rebecca? You thought that?

1363
01:31:26,217 --> 01:31:28,198
我恨她
I hated her.

1364
01:31:40,294 --> 01:31:42,786
我曾为她着迷
Oh,I was carried away by her,enchanted by her as everyone was.

1365
01:31:42,796 --> 01:31:45,507
为她心醉  跟所有人一样

1366
01:31:45,507 --> 01:31:50,304
我娶她的时候  别人都说我是世界上最幸运的男人
And when I was married,I was told I was the luckiest man in the world.

1367
01:31:53,119 --> 01:31:55,622
她长得那么美
She was so lovely,so accomplished,

1368
01:31:55,622 --> 01:31:58,854
很聪明  很风趣

1369
01:31:57,303 --> 01:31:58,668
so amusing.

1370
01:31:58,854 --> 01:32:02,253
大家都说
“She’s got the three things that really matter in a wife,”everyone said.

1371
01:32:02,253 --> 01:32:03,223
"一个妻子得有三种美德"
“Breeding brains and beauty.”

1372
01:32:03,234 --> 01:32:05,840
"教养  头脑和姿色"

1373
01:32:05,840 --> 01:32:09,073
我完全相信了他们的话
And I believed them. Completely.

1374
01:32:10,532 --> 01:32:13,661
但跟她在一起我从未有过幸福的时刻
But I never had a moment’s happiness with her.

1375
01:32:13,661 --> 01:32:16,476
她不懂爱
She was incapable of love

1376
01:32:16,476 --> 01:32:20,021
或是温柔或是宽容
or tenderness

1377
01:32:18,450 --> 01:32:19,815
or decency.

1378
01:32:21,377 --> 01:32:24,494
你不爱她?  你不爱她?
You didn’t love her. You didn’t love her.

1379
01:32:24,505 --> 01:32:29,197
还记得那天我开车带你上蒙特卡洛山顶的情景吗
Do you remember that cliff where you first saw me in Monte Carlo?

1380
01:32:29,197 --> 01:32:32,638
我曾跟丽贝卡一起到那儿度蜜月
Well. I went there with Rebecca on our honeymoon.

1381
01:32:32,638 --> 01:32:35,453
那就是我们相遇的地方
That’s where I found out about her,four days after we were married.

1382
01:32:35,453 --> 01:32:38,373
4天后我们就结婚了

1383
01:32:38,477 --> 01:32:40,980
她站在那儿笑
She stood there laughing,her black hair blowing in the wind

1384
01:32:41,084 --> 01:32:43,586
她的一头黑发在风中吹起

1385
01:32:43,691 --> 01:32:46,714
告诉我所有有关她的事
and told me all about herself.Everything.

1386
01:32:46,714 --> 01:32:48,696
所有事

1387
01:32:50,677 --> 01:32:53,899
我绝不会告诉别人
Things I’ll never tell a living soul.

1388
01:32:53,909 --> 01:32:55,890
我想要杀了她
I wanted to kill her.

1389
01:32:56,099 --> 01:32:59,018
那太容易了  记得那个悬崖吗
It would have been so easy.You remember the precipice?

1390
01:33:01,000 --> 01:33:05,369
我吓到你了  对吧  你以为我疯了
I frightened you,didn’t I? You thought I was mad.

1391
01:33:05,379 --> 01:33:08,924
说不定我也确实是个疯子
Perhaps I was. Perhaps I am mad.

1392
01:33:10,384 --> 01:33:13,721
跟魔鬼一起生活的人神智不可能健全  对吗
It wouldn’t make for sanity,would it? Living with the devil?

1393
01:33:16,849 --> 01:33:19,560
她说"我要跟你做笔交易"
“I’ll make a bargain with you,” she said.

1394
01:33:19,560 --> 01:33:21,270
"刚结婚4天你就想跟我离婚"
“You’d look rather foolish trying to divorce me now

1395
01:33:21,270 --> 01:33:23,199
"你看来相当的愚蠢"
after four days of marriage,

1396
01:33:23,209 --> 01:33:25,149
"所以我会扮演一位贤妻"
so I’ll play the part of a devoted wife,

1397
01:33:25,149 --> 01:33:26,963
"你珍贵的曼陀丽庄园的女主人"
mistress of your precious Manderley.

1398
01:33:26,963 --> 01:33:27,797
"只要你愿意
I’ll make it the most famous showplace is England,if you like,

1399
01:33:27,797 --> 01:33:30,091
我可以使这所宅子成为全国首屈一指的闻名去处"

1400
01:33:30,091 --> 01:33:32,385
"人们会跑来做客  羡慕我们 "
and people will visit us and envy us,

1401
01:33:32,385 --> 01:33:35,409
"在背地议论说我们俩是全英国最幸运  最美满的一对"
and say we’re the luckiest,happiest couple is the courtry.

1402
01:33:37,077 --> 01:33:40,414
"多大的愚弄  同时又是多大的成功"
What a grand joke it’ll be. What a triumph,”

1403
01:33:45,002 --> 01:33:49,277
我不该接受她那肮脏的交易  可我还是接受了
I should never have accepted her dirty bargain,but I did.

1404
01:33:50,737 --> 01:33:55,002
当时我过于年轻气盛  太过于在乎家族荣誉
I was younger then,and tremendously conscious of the family honor.

1405
01:33:55,012 --> 01:33:58,453
家族荣誉
Family honor.

1406
01:33:58,453 --> 01:34:00,434
她知道我宁愿牺牲一切
She knew that I'd sacrifice everything rather than stand up in a divorce court

1407
01:34:00,434 --> 01:34:02,519
也不要站在离婚法庭上

1408
01:34:02,519 --> 01:34:05,960
抛弃她  承认我们的婚姻是一场诈欺婚姻
and give her away,admit that our marriage was a rotten fraud.

1409
01:34:08,671 --> 01:34:12,415
你鄙弃我  是吗  连我自己都鄙弃我自己
You despise me,don’t you?

1410
01:34:10,603 --> 01:34:11,638
As I despise myself

1411
01:34:12,425 --> 01:34:17,743
你无法明白我什么感受  你能吗
You can’t understand what my feelings were,

1412
01:34:15,984 --> 01:34:16,973
can you?

1413
01:34:19,307 --> 01:34:22,227
我当然能明白  亲爱的  我当然明白
Of course I can,darling. Of course I can.

1414
01:34:24,625 --> 01:34:27,951
我遵守协议  显然她也是
Well,I kept the bargain and so did she,apparently.

1415
01:34:27,962 --> 01:34:30,568
她非常遵守游戏规则
Oh,she played the game brilliantly,

1416
01:34:30,568 --> 01:34:33,592
但不久  她慢慢地放肆起来
but after a while,she began to grow careless.

1417
01:34:33,592 --> 01:34:37,023
她在伦敦买了一套公寓  定期会在那儿住几天
She took a flat in London,and she'd stay away for days at a time.

1418
01:34:37,033 --> 01:34:39,744
她开始把自己的一帮狐群狗党请到这儿来
Then she started to bring her friends down here.

1419
01:34:39,744 --> 01:34:42,142
我向她提出过警告   她却毫不在意地一耸肩
I warned her,but she shrugged her shoulders.

1420
01:34:42,142 --> 01:34:44,541
说"这跟你有什么关系"
“What’s it got to do with you?” she said.

1421
01:34:44,541 --> 01:34:49,327
后来她竟同弗兰克调起情来  可怜的  忠实朋友
She even started on Frank.

1422
01:34:46,347 --> 01:34:47,962
Poor,faithful Frank.

1423
01:34:49,337 --> 01:34:53,404
她有个表哥  此人名叫费弗尔
Then there was a cousin of hers,a man named Favell.

1424
01:34:53,404 --> 01:34:56,834
我认识这个人  你去伦敦那天他来过
Yes. I know him. He came the day you went to London.

1425
01:34:56,845 --> 01:34:59,451
干吗不告诉我
Why didn’t you tell me?

1426
01:34:59,451 --> 01:35:04,863
我不想告诉你  我怕一说又会惹起你对丽贝卡的回忆
I didn’t like to.

1427
01:35:01,279 --> 01:35:03,770
I thought it would remind you of Rebecca.

1428
01:35:04,873 --> 01:35:08,314
惹起我的回忆?
Remind me?

1429
01:35:08,314 --> 01:35:11,432
难道我还要别人来惹起回忆吗
As if I needed reminding.

1430
01:35:11,443 --> 01:35:14,675
费弗尔常常来这间小屋探望她
Favell used to visit her here in this cottage.

1431
01:35:14,675 --> 01:35:17,386
我发现了此事  又一次提出警告
I found out about it,and I warmed her that if he come here again,

1432
01:35:17,386 --> 01:35:20,410
如果他再来这儿  我会开枪打死他们俩
I’d shoot them both.

1433
01:35:20,410 --> 01:35:24,779
某夜当我发现她悄悄从伦敦回来的时候
One night,when I found she had come back quietly from London,

1434
01:35:24,789 --> 01:35:26,875
我以为费弗尔跟她在一起
I thought that Favell was with her,

1435
01:35:26,875 --> 01:35:29,002
我知道我已无法再忍受
and I knew then that I couldn’t stand

1436
01:35:29,002 --> 01:35:31,880
这种充满污秽和欺诈的生活
this life of filth and deceit any longer.

1437
01:35:33,235 --> 01:35:37,510
我决定过来跟他们俩同归于尽
I decided to come down here and have it out with both of them.

1438
01:35:39,387 --> 01:35:41,368
但她独自一人
But she was alone.

1439
01:35:41,368 --> 01:35:44,392
她在盼望费弗尔的到来  但他没有
She was expecting Favell,but he hadn’t come.

1440
01:35:44,392 --> 01:35:46,686
她躺在长沙发椅上
She was lying on the divan,a large tray of cigarette stubs beside her.

1441
01:35:46,686 --> 01:35:50,127
一大盘掐灭的的烟头放在她旁边

1442
01:35:50,127 --> 01:35:53,140
她看上去生病了  不舒服
She looked ill,queer.

1443
01:35:53,151 --> 01:35:55,549
她突然起身
Suddenly,she got up,started to walk toward me.

1444
01:35:55,549 --> 01:35:58,364
开始向我走来

1445
01:35:58,364 --> 01:36:00,658
她说  "假如我有个孩子"
“When I have a child,”she said,“neither you nor anyone else

1446
01:36:00,658 --> 01:36:03,891
"你跟我都无法证明孩子不是你生的"
could ever prove it wasn’t yours.

1447
01:36:03,891 --> 01:36:06,571
"迈克斯  你想要个继承人  不是吗"
You would like to have an heir,wouldn’t you,Max,

1448
01:36:06,571 --> 01:36:08,364
"为了你钟爱的曼陀丽"
for your precious Manderley?”

1449
01:36:08,374 --> 01:36:10,356
她开始放声大笑
Then she started to laugh.

1450
01:36:10,356 --> 01:36:13,901
"多有趣  真是有趣到极点  妙不可言"
“How funny.How supremely,wonderfully funny.

1451
01:36:13,901 --> 01:36:15,684
"我将做一个十全十美的良母
I’ll be the perfect mother,just as I’ve been the perfect wife.

1452
01:36:15,684 --> 01:36:17,238
就像我是个十全十美的贤妻"
No one will ever know.

1453
01:36:17,238 --> 01:36:19,323
"谁也不会了解事实真相"
It ought to give you the thrill of your life,Max,

1454
01:36:19,323 --> 01:36:21,825
"那应该会使你的生活充满恐惧  迈克斯"
to watch my son grow bigger day by day

1455
01:36:21,825 --> 01:36:24,526
"看着我的儿子一天天长大 "

1456
01:36:24,536 --> 01:36:28,603
"一旦你死了  这一切将全部都归他所有"
and to know that when you die,Manderley will be his.”

1457
01:36:28,603 --> 01:36:31,835
她面对着我
She was face to face with me.

1458
01:36:31,835 --> 01:36:34,328
一只手插在口袋里
One hand is her pocket,the other holding a cigarette.

1459
01:36:34,338 --> 01:36:37,258
另一只手拿着香烟

1460
01:36:36,632 --> 01:36:38,927
微笑着
She was smiling.

1461
01:36:38,927 --> 01:36:42,891
"迈克斯  你将会怎么做"
“Well,Max?

1462
01:36:40,753 --> 01:36:43,290
What are you going to do about it?

1463
01:36:44,458 --> 01:36:47,275
"难道你要杀了我吗"
Aren’t you going to kill me?”

1464
01:36:48,841 --> 01:36:51,345
我猜想那一刻我失去理智了
I suppose I went mad for a moment.

1465
01:36:53,015 --> 01:36:55,414
我必须打她
I must have struck her.

1466
01:36:58,858 --> 01:37:01,675
她站在那儿盯着我
She stood staring at me.

1467
01:37:01,677 --> 01:37:04,807
她看起来几近得意洋洋
She looked almost triumphant.

1468
01:37:06,372 --> 01:37:10,535
然后她又开始微笑着向我走来
Then she started toward me again. Smiling.

1469
01:37:10,547 --> 01:37:13,259
突然她绊倒了
Suddenly,she stumbled and fell.

1470
01:37:18,791 --> 01:37:20,981
过了很久  当我低头看的时候
When I looked down,

1471
01:37:20,982 --> 01:37:23,371
好像 她正躺在地上
ages afterwards,it seemed,she was lying on the floor.

1472
01:37:23,383 --> 01:37:28,287
她将她的头往一块很重的船用索具上撞
She had struck her head on a heavy piece of ship’s tackle.

1473
01:37:30,271 --> 01:37:34,340
我依然记得当时纳闷她为何仍然在微笑
I rememder wondering why she was still smilling.

1474
01:37:34,340 --> 01:37:36,530
然后我才意识到她已经死了
Then I realized she was dead.

1475
01:37:36,531 --> 01:37:39,766
但你没有杀她  那是一场意外
But you didn’t kill her.It was an accident.

1476
01:37:39,767 --> 01:37:44,242
谁会相信我  我不知所措
Who would believe me?

1477
01:37:44,254 --> 01:37:47,895
我只知道我得做些什么事  任何事
I lost my head.

1478
01:37:44,692 --> 01:37:47,684
I just knew I had to do something. Anything.

1479
01:37:47,906 --> 01:37:51,141
我把她的尸体拖上了船
I carried her out to the boat.

1480
01:37:51,141 --> 01:37:55,095
外面一片漆黑  那晚上没有月光
It was very dark. There was no moon.

1481
01:37:55,107 --> 01:37:57,611
我把她的尸体拖进船舱
I put her in the cabin.

1482
01:37:57,612 --> 01:37:59,928
当船看起来离岸有一段安全距离的时候
When the boat seemed a safe distance from the shore,I took a spike,

1483
01:37:59,928 --> 01:38:00,428
我拿了一枚大钉
and drove it again and again through the planking of the hull.

1484
01:38:00,428 --> 01:38:03,443
然后一直猛击船板

1485
01:38:03,455 --> 01:38:06,784
我打开通海阀  水开始快速流进来
I had opened up the seacocks and the water began to come in fast.

1486
01:38:06,795 --> 01:38:10,029
我爬进小船里  划走
I climbed over into the dinghy and pulled away.

1487
01:38:10,031 --> 01:38:14,830
我看着船倾斜 下沉
I saw the boat heel over

1488
01:38:14,013 --> 01:38:15,253
and sink.

1489
01:38:17,230 --> 01:38:20,569
我折回到小海湾
I pulled back into the cove.

1490
01:38:20,570 --> 01:38:23,282
天开始下雨
It started raining.

1491
01:38:23,282 --> 01:38:26,099
迈克西姆  有别人知道这事吗
-Maxim,does anyone else know of this? -No. No one except you and me.

1492
01:38:26,101 --> 01:38:28,813
没有  除了你跟我  没人知道

1493
01:38:30,170 --> 01:38:32,153
我们必须去解释清楚
We must explain it.

1494
01:38:32,154 --> 01:38:35,492
因为那具尸体你之前从未见过
It’s got to be the body of someone you’ve never seen before.

1495
01:38:35,492 --> 01:38:37,475
不  他们一定认识她
No,they’re bound to know her. Her rings,bracelets she always wore.

1496
01:38:37,580 --> 01:38:40,605
她一直戴的戒指  手镯

1497
01:38:40,607 --> 01:38:45,396
他们会认出她的尸体  然后他们会记起另一个女人
They’ll identify her body then they’ll remember the other woman.

1498
01:38:45,407 --> 01:38:48,735
另一个埋葬在墓地里的女人
The other woman buried in the crypt.

1499
01:38:48,746 --> 01:38:51,041
如果他们发现那是丽贝卡
If they find out it was Rebecca,

1500
01:38:51,042 --> 01:38:54,381
你必须说你认错尸了
you must simply say you made a mistake about the other body.

1501
01:38:54,382 --> 01:38:56,062
因为你去埃奇库姆的那天  你正发病
That the day you went to Edgecombe,you were ill,

1502
01:38:56,062 --> 01:38:57,407
不能对自己的所作所为负责
you didn’t know what you were doind.

1503
01:38:57,408 --> 01:38:59,703
丽贝卡已死  那才是我们要记住的事
Rebecca’s dead.That’s what we’ve got to rememdar.Rebecca’s dead.

1504
01:38:59,703 --> 01:39:01,790
丽贝卡已死  她无法再开口讲话
She can't speak. She can't bear witness. She can't harm you anymore.

1505
01:39:01,792 --> 01:39:04,087
死无对证  她无法再伤害你了

1506
01:39:04,087 --> 01:39:07,217
天知地知  你知我知
We’re the only two people in the worlh thet know,Maxiw,yon and I.

1507
01:39:07,217 --> 01:39:10,754
我曾告诉过你  娶你为妻  是我多么自私的行为
I'd told you once that I’d done a selfish thing in marrying you.

1508
01:39:10,766 --> 01:39:13,791
现在你能明白什么意思了
You can understand now what I meant.

1509
01:39:13,792 --> 01:39:16,817
我爱你  亲爱的
I’ve loved you,my darling.

1510
01:39:16,819 --> 01:39:19,010
我会永远爱你
I shall always love you,

1511
01:39:19,010 --> 01:39:24,008
但我自始至终都知道丽贝卡最终会赢
but I’ve known all along

1512
01:39:21,622 --> 01:39:23,613
that Rebecca would win in the end.

1513
01:39:24,018 --> 01:39:26,417
不  不  她没有赢
No. no. She hasn't won.

1514
01:39:26,419 --> 01:39:29,967
不管现在发生什么事  她都没有赢
No matter what happens now,she hasn’t won.

1515
01:39:30,465 --> 01:39:32,205
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

1516
01:39:43,742 --> 01:39:46,141
喂?  喂
Hello?

1517
01:39:47,396 --> 01:39:50,943
喂  弗兰克  喂  弗兰克  是
Hello. Frank.

1518
01:39:48,983 --> 01:39:50,393
Hello,Frank. Yes.

1519
01:39:51,047 --> 01:39:53,655
谁  卡洛祖兰?
Who? Colonel Julyan?

1520
01:39:53,656 --> 01:39:57,933
告诉他我会尽快去那儿见他
Yes. Tell him I’ll meet him there as soon as I possibly can.

1521
01:39:57,935 --> 01:40:01,587
什么
What?

1522
01:40:01,587 --> 01:40:06,699
就说等我们确定事态后再谈
Well...

1523
01:40:02,830 --> 01:40:06,448
Say we could talk about that when we’re sure about the matter.

1524
01:40:10,250 --> 01:40:12,649
怎么了
What’s happened?

1525
01:40:12,649 --> 01:40:17,438
卡洛祖兰召见  他是国家郡警察局长
Colonel Julyan called.

1526
01:40:15,134 --> 01:40:17,500
He’s the chief constable of the county.

1527
01:40:17,449 --> 01:40:20,996
他被警察局请去停尸间
He’s been asked by the police to go to the mortuary.

1528
01:40:20,998 --> 01:40:25,171
他想知道我是否有可能认错了
He wanted to know if I could possibly have made a mistake

1529
01:40:25,171 --> 01:40:27,466
那具尸体
about that other body.

1530
01:40:47,399 --> 01:40:48,505
卡洛祖兰
Well,Colonel Julyan,apparently I did make a mistake about that other body.

1531
01:40:48,507 --> 01:40:51,668
显然我是认错尸体了

1532
01:40:51,679 --> 01:40:54,599
在那种情况之下  弄错很自然
Tha mistake was natural under the circumstances.

1533
01:40:54,600 --> 01:40:58,043
-再说  那时你状态不好  -我当时状态很好
-Besides,you weren’t well at the time. -That’s nonsense. I was perfectly well.

1534
01:40:58,044 --> 01:41:00,235
别担心  迈克西姆
Don’t let it worry you,Maxim. Nobody can blame you for making a mistake.

1535
01:41:00,235 --> 01:41:02,947
没人会因你搞错而责怪你

1536
01:41:03,052 --> 01:41:06,798
可惜的是  你得重新经受同样的事
The pity is,you’ve got to go through the same thing all over again.

1537
01:41:06,810 --> 01:41:09,941
-什么意思  -理所当然  将会有另一次审讯
What do you mean?

1538
01:41:07,395 --> 01:41:11,138
There’ll have to be another inquest,of course. Same formality and red tape.

1539
01:41:09,941 --> 01:41:12,861
同样的手续跟繁杂的公事程序

1540
01:41:12,863 --> 01:41:14,752
我希望你可以避免公众对它的主意
Wish you could be spared the publicity of it,but I’m afraid that's impossible.

1541
01:41:14,752 --> 01:41:16,086
但我恐怕那很难办到
Oh,yes,publicity.

1542
01:41:16,098 --> 01:41:18,601
对  公众的主意

1543
01:41:18,601 --> 01:41:21,418
我猜想德温特太太走下甲板去拿东西
I suppose Mrs.de Winter went below for something and a squall hit the boat

1544
01:41:21,420 --> 01:41:24,759
然后无人掌舵的船遭遇飓风
with nobody at the helm.

1545
01:41:24,759 --> 01:41:27,983
我猜想是那么回事  你觉得呢  克劳莱
I imagine that’s about the solution now,don’t you think so,Crawley?

1546
01:41:27,995 --> 01:41:31,438
是的  可能门卡住了  她无法再回到甲板上
Oh,yes. Probably the door jammed,and she couldn't get on deck again.

1547
01:41:31,438 --> 01:41:33,420
对  泰伯  那个造船的人
Yeah.

1548
01:41:31,210 --> 01:41:35,078
Tabb,the boat builder,will undoubtedly come to some such conclusion.

1549
01:41:33,420 --> 01:41:35,924
毫无疑问会得出一些这样的结论

1550
01:41:35,926 --> 01:41:38,534
为什么  他会知道些什么
Why,what would he know about it?

1551
01:41:38,535 --> 01:41:40,517
他现在在检查船只
Well,he’s examining the boat now. Purely as a matter of routine,you know.

1552
01:41:40,621 --> 01:41:42,708
完全按照惯例

1553
01:41:42,709 --> 01:41:46,673
明天我会进行审讯  迈克西姆  完全非正式的
I’ll be at the inquest tomorrow,Maxim,quite unofficially,you know.

1554
01:41:46,674 --> 01:41:49,689
等所有事都结束了  我们必须一起打场高尔夫
We must get together for a game of golf when it’s all over,eh?

1555
01:41:49,701 --> 01:41:51,892
-好  -再见
Bys-bye.

1556
01:42:04,205 --> 01:42:06,500
我有晚报  夫人
I have the evening papers,madam. Would you care to see them?

1557
01:42:06,502 --> 01:42:08,797
-要看看吗  -不  谢谢  弗里思
Oh,no thank you,Frith,

1558
01:42:08,902 --> 01:42:11,614
还有我想德温特先生也不会想看
and I prefer that Mr.de Winter weren’t troubled with them,either.

1559
01:42:11,615 --> 01:42:12,459
明白  夫人
I understand,madaw. Permit me to say that we’re all most distressed outside.

1560
01:42:12,461 --> 01:42:14,944
请允许我说句话  我们都承受着外界最巨大的困扰

1561
01:42:14,955 --> 01:42:16,122
谢谢  弗里思
Thank you,Frith.

1562
01:42:16,123 --> 01:42:18,919
恐怕那些新闻使丹弗斯太太受惊了
I’m afraid the news has been a great shock to Mrs. Danvers.

1563
01:42:18,920 --> 01:42:21,424
是啊  我多少预料到了
Yes,I rather expected it would be.

1564
01:42:21,426 --> 01:42:24,242
好像有一场验尸官审讯会  夫人
It seems there’s to be a coroner’s inquest,madam?

1565
01:42:24,242 --> 01:42:26,954
是的  弗里思  完全出于形式的审讯
Yes,Frith.It’s purely a formality

1566
01:42:26,955 --> 01:42:29,563
当然  夫人  我  我想说
Of course,madam. I...

1567
01:42:29,565 --> 01:42:32,486
如果我们任何人可能被传唤取证
I wanted to say that if any of us might be required to give avidence,

1568
01:42:32,487 --> 01:42:35,825
我将会很乐意做任何可能帮到家族的事
I should be only too pleased to do anything that might help the family.

1569
01:42:35,827 --> 01:42:37,611
谢谢  弗里思  我肯定
Oh,thank you,Frith,why,I...

1570
01:42:37,611 --> 01:42:39,780
德温特先生会很开心听到这席话
I’m sure Mr.de Winter will be very happy to hear it.

1571
01:42:39,792 --> 01:42:42,922
但我不认为有任何必要
But I don’t think anything will be necessary.

1572
01:42:55,758 --> 01:42:57,740
迈克西姆
Maxim.

1573
01:42:58,785 --> 01:43:00,871
亲爱的
Hello,darling.

1574
01:43:00,872 --> 01:43:05,557
迈克西姆  我 我担心明天在审讯会上你会做什么
Oh,Maxim,I’m worried about what you’ll do at the inquest tomorrow.

1575
01:43:05,569 --> 01:43:07,551
什么意思
What do you mean?

1576
01:43:07,655 --> 01:43:09,950
你不会发脾气吧
You won’t lose your temper,will you?

1577
01:43:09,950 --> 01:43:12,767
向我保证他们不会令你发火
Promise me that they won’t make you angry.

1578
01:43:12,768 --> 01:43:15,271
好的  亲爱的  我保证
All right,darling.I promise.

1579
01:43:15,273 --> 01:43:18,925
不管他问你什么  你不会失去理智
No matter what he asks you,you won’t lose your head?

1580
01:43:18,925 --> 01:43:21,428
别担心  亲爱的
Don’t worry,dear.

1581
01:43:21,430 --> 01:43:24,351
他们无法马上都搞定  对吗
They can’t do anything at once,can they?

1582
01:43:23,364 --> 01:43:25,070
No.

1583
01:43:26,334 --> 01:43:29,871
-那我们还剩一点时间在一起?  -是的
Then we’ve a little time left to be together.

1584
01:43:27,660 --> 01:43:28,820
Yes.

1585
01:43:29,884 --> 01:43:33,431
我想要跟你一起去审讯会
-I want to go to the inquest with you. -I’d rather you didn’t,darling.

1586
01:43:33,431 --> 01:43:35,100
我宁愿你不去  亲爱的
But I can't wait here alone.

1587
01:43:35,100 --> 01:43:37,291
但我无法一个人在这儿等着

1588
01:43:37,292 --> 01:43:40,317
我向你保证我不会给你带来任何麻烦的
I promise you,I won’t be any trouble to you.

1589
01:43:40,318 --> 01:43:43,970
不管发生什么事我必须待在你身边
And I must be near you so that no matter what happens,

1590
01:43:43,972 --> 01:43:47,102
我们片刻都不会分离
we won’t be separated for a moment.

1591
01:43:47,102 --> 01:43:49,084
好吧  亲爱的
All right,dear.

1592
01:43:51,066 --> 01:43:54,395
这整件事我都不在乎  除了你
I don’t mind this whole thing except for you.

1593
01:43:54,407 --> 01:43:57,642
我无法忘怀对你所做的事
I can't forget what it’s done to you.

1594
01:43:57,642 --> 01:44:01,293
自从它发生以来  我别无它想
I’ve been thinking of nothing else since it happened.

1595
01:44:04,529 --> 01:44:07,032
永远都回不去了
It’s gone forever,

1596
01:44:07,034 --> 01:44:12,136
我所爱的风趣  年轻貌美
that funny,young,lost look I loved.

1597
01:44:12,147 --> 01:44:14,233
永远不会再回来了
It won’t ever come back.

1598
01:44:15,487 --> 01:44:18,825
当我告诉你有关丽贝卡的事时  就被我抹杀了
I killed that when I told you about Rebecca.

1599
01:44:18,826 --> 01:44:21,320
都离开了
It’s gone.

1600
01:44:21,330 --> 01:44:24,355
在几个小时之内
In a few hours,you’ve grown so much older.

1601
01:44:24,357 --> 01:44:26,965
你变得更成熟了

1602
01:44:28,427 --> 01:44:31,452
迈克西姆  迈克西姆
(SOBBING)Oh,Maxim Maxim.

1603
01:44:56,812 --> 01:44:58,899
布莱克杰克・布莱德是他的名字
Black Jack Brady was his name.

1604
01:44:58,899 --> 01:45:01,507
我曾办过的最重要的案件
The most important arrest I ever made.

1605
01:45:01,613 --> 01:45:04,012
2年之前的案件
It must have been about two years ago now.

1606
01:45:04,012 --> 01:45:05,994
当然毫无疑问
Of course,there was no doubt about it. He was hung a month after I caught him.

1607
01:45:05,995 --> 01:45:08,499
我逮捕他1个月后  他被处以绞刑
Hello. Wait a minute.

1608
01:45:08,500 --> 01:45:10,899
等一下

1609
01:45:10,900 --> 01:45:13,300
他们带老伯米・本上来了
They’ve got old Balmy Ben up now.

1610
01:45:13,300 --> 01:45:16,325
你记得前任德温特太太吧
CORONER: You remember the late Mrs.de Winter,don’t you?

1611
01:45:16,327 --> 01:45:18,726
-她死了  -是的  我们知道
-She’s gone. -Yes,we know that.

1612
01:45:18,727 --> 01:45:21,543
她出海  被大海吞噬了
-She went in the sea. The sea got her. -That's right.That’s right.

1613
01:45:21,544 --> 01:45:24,465
对的 我们想要你告诉我们
Now we want you to tell us whether you were on the shore

1614
01:45:24,467 --> 01:45:27,377
那晚她出海  你是否在岸边
-that last night she went sailing. -Eh?

1615
01:45:27,389 --> 01:45:29,788
那晚她出去
Were you on the shore that last sight she went ou,when she didn't come back?

1616
01:45:29,892 --> 01:45:32,802
当她没返回的时候  你在岸边吗

1617
01:45:32,815 --> 01:45:37,092
我什么都没看见  我不想要去精神病院
I didn’t see nothing. I don’t want to go to the asylum.

1618
01:45:37,093 --> 01:45:39,388
那儿有恶人
Them cruel folks there.

1619
01:45:39,495 --> 01:45:41,894
没人要送你去精神病院
Now,nobody’s going to send you to the asylum.

1620
01:45:41,894 --> 01:45:44,502
我们只想要你告诉我们你所见到的
All we want you to do is tell us what you saw.

1621
01:45:44,503 --> 01:45:46,172
我什么也没看到
I didn’t see nothing.

1622
01:45:46,173 --> 01:45:50,858
快点  你有看到德温特太太那晚有上她的船吗
CORONER: Come,come.

1623
01:45:47,132 --> 01:45:50,920
Did you see Mrs.de Winter get into her boat that last night?

1624
01:45:50,868 --> 01:45:56,398
我什么都不知道  我不想去精神病院
I don’t know nothing.

1625
01:45:53,472 --> 01:45:55,884
I don’t want to go to the asylum.

1626
01:45:59,426 --> 01:46:01,825
好了  你可以走了
Very well.You may go.

1627
01:46:01,826 --> 01:46:04,538
你可以走了
-Eh? -You may go now.

1628
01:46:04,644 --> 01:46:08,608
