-Mr.Tabb,step forward,please. -Yes?

1629
01:46:11,636 --> 01:46:13,670
你所说的证供属实
The evidence you give will be the truth,the whole truth

1630
01:46:13,670 --> 01:46:16,018
绝无半点虚假
and nothing but the truth,so help you God?

1631
01:46:16,020 --> 01:46:18,930
我敢向上帝发誓
I do,so help me God.

1632
01:46:18,940 --> 01:46:19,503
前任德温特太太
The late Mrs.de Winter used to send her boat

1633
01:46:19,504 --> 01:46:22,801
过去常常把她的船送到你的船坞调修
-to your shipyard for reconditioning. -That’s right,sir.

1634
01:46:22,801 --> 01:46:25,722
-是的  长官  -你还记得任何
CORONER: Can you remember any occasion

1635
01:46:25,724 --> 01:46:28,540
-当她开船造成船只出任何意外的原因吗  -没有  长官
when she had any sort of accident with the boat?

1636
01:46:28,542 --> 01:46:30,524
我经常说德温特太太是个天生的水手
TABB: No,sir. I often said Mrs.de Winter was a born sailor.

1637
01:46:30,524 --> 01:46:33,444
当德温特太太走下甲板的时候  假设
Now,when Mrs.de Winter went below,as is supposed,

1638
01:46:33,446 --> 01:46:35,533
一场突如其来的飓风刮来
and a sudden gust of wind came down,

1639
01:46:35,533 --> 01:46:38,454
足以把船吹翻  不是吗
that would be enough to capsize the boat,wouldn’t it?

1640
01:46:38,455 --> 01:46:41,679
不好意思  长官  但还有其它的原因
Excuse we,sir. But there's a little more to it than that.

1641
01:46:41,690 --> 01:46:45,133
-什么意思  泰伯先生  -长官  我是说通海阀
-What do you mean,Mr.Tabb? -I mean,sir,the seacocks.

1642
01:46:45,134 --> 01:46:47,429
-什么是通海阀  -通海阀
What are the seacocks?

1643
01:46:47,430 --> 01:46:52,219
通海阀是船抽水的阀门
Sea...

1644
01:46:48,611 --> 01:46:51,819
The seacocks are the valves to drain out the boat.

1645
01:46:52,230 --> 01:46:56,810
当你在海上航行的时候  它们一直都是紧闭着的
They’re always kept tight closed when you’re afloat.

1646
01:46:56,822 --> 01:46:58,387
然后呢
Yes?

1647
01:46:58,491 --> 01:47:01,934
昨天当我检查船只的时候  我发现它们被打开了
Well,yesterday,when I examined that boat,I found they’d been opened.

1648
01:47:01,936 --> 01:47:05,171
-会有什么后果  -就是这样
Whet could be the reason for that?

1649
01:47:03,375 --> 01:47:06,742
Just this,that’s what flooded the boat and sunk her.

1650
01:47:05,171 --> 01:47:09,125
水渗进来把她淹没了

1651
01:47:09,135 --> 01:47:12,672
-你是指   -船根本就不是被吹翻的
Are you implying that boat never capsized at all?

1652
01:47:12,685 --> 01:47:15,605
长官  我知道这么不应该
I know it’s a terrible thing to say,sir,but in my opinion,

1653
01:47:15,606 --> 01:47:19,049
但依我所见  她是被淹没的
she was scuttled.

1654
01:47:21,137 --> 01:47:24,580
-还有洞  -什么洞
-And there’s them holes. -What holes?

1655
01:47:24,686 --> 01:47:27,492
-在她的翼板上  -你在说什么
-Is her planking. -What are you talking about?

1656
01:47:27,503 --> 01:47:31,154
当然  船已经在水下超过一年
Of course,that boat’s been underwater for over a year,

1657
01:47:31,155 --> 01:47:34,494
潮水使她的船撞到海脊
and the tide’s been knocking her against the ridge.

1658
01:47:34,495 --> 01:47:38,668
但是那些裂口看起来好像是她从里面造成的
But it seemed to me them holes looked as if she’d made them from the inside.

1659
01:47:40,339 --> 01:47:43,364
那么你认为她肯定是故意弄出来的
Then you believe she must have done it deliberately.

1660
01:47:43,365 --> 01:47:47,434
以她对船的知识  不可能会出此意外
Couldn’t have been no accident not with her knowledge of boats.

1661
01:47:49,418 --> 01:47:52,328
我相信  你对前任德温特太太很了解吧
You know the former Mrs.de Winter very well,I believe?

1662
01:47:50,756 --> 01:47:51,666
Oh,yes.

1663
01:47:52,340 --> 01:47:55,887
-是的  -你相信她会有自杀倾向吗
Would you have believed her capable of suicide?

1664
01:47:55,888 --> 01:47:59,018
不  坦白讲我不相信  但这很难说
No.Frankly,I would not. But you never can tell.

1665
01:47:59,018 --> 01:48:01,835
你可以下去了  泰伯先生
You way stand down,Mr.Tabb.

1666
01:48:02,985 --> 01:48:05,593
