抱歉又把你拉回来做进一步审讯
(GAVEL POUNDING)

1669
01:48:13,487 --> 01:48:15,694
Sorry to drag you back for furthur questioning,Mr.de Winter.

1670
01:48:16,655 --> 01:48:18,303
你已经听到泰伯先生的陈述了
But you’ve heard the statement of Mr.Tabb.

1671
01:48:18,304 --> 01:48:20,099
我想知道你是否能给予帮助
I wonder if you can help us in any way.

1672
01:48:20,099 --> 01:48:22,801
-恐怖帮不上忙  -你能想到为何会有洞吗
I’m afraid not.

1673
01:48:20,369 --> 01:48:21,984
Can you think of any reason why there should be holes

1674
01:48:22,916 --> 01:48:25,628
前任德温特太太的船船板上的洞
in the planking of the late Mrs.de Winter’s boat?

1675
01:48:25,630 --> 01:48:27,925
我当然想不出任何原因
Well,of course I can't think of any reason.

1676
01:48:27,925 --> 01:48:30,742
之前有人曾跟你谈论过这些洞吗
Has anyone ever discussed these holes with you before?

1677
01:48:30,743 --> 01:48:33,361
自从船沉于海底以来
Well,since the boat has been at the bottom of the ocean,

1678
01:48:31,463 --> 01:48:33,044
I scarcely think that likely.

1679
01:48:33,363 --> 01:48:34,698
我几乎不可能想过
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

1680
01:48:34,708 --> 01:48:38,256
德温特先生  我想你相信我们都为你感到难过
Mr.be Winter,I want you to believe we all feel very deeply

1681
01:48:36,510 --> 01:48:37,499
for you in this matter.

1682
01:48:38,257 --> 01:48:40,760
但我不是为了自己的娱乐而举行这场审讯
But you must remember that I don’t conduct this inquiry

1683
01:48:40,760 --> 01:48:43,264
-显而易见  不是吗  -希望如此
for my own amusement.

1684
01:48:40,681 --> 01:48:42,546
-That’s rather obvious,isn’t it? -I hope that it is.

1685
01:48:43,266 --> 01:48:44,852
因为德温特太太单独出海
Well,since she went sailing alone,

1686
01:48:44,852 --> 01:48:46,907
难道我们就认为是她自己凿的那些洞吗
are we to believe that she drove those doles herself?

1687
01:48:46,917 --> 01:48:48,691
随你怎么想
You may believe what you like.

1688
01:48:48,797 --> 01:48:50,675
你可以启发我们关于德温特太太为何
Can you enlighten us as to why Mrs.de Winter should have wanted

1689
01:48:50,780 --> 01:48:52,762
想要结束她自己的生命
to end her own life?

1690
01:48:52,866 --> 01:48:54,848
我不知道什么原因
I know of no reason whatever.

1691
01:48:54,849 --> 01:48:57,144
德温特先生  不管有多么痛苦
Mr.de Winter,however painful it may be,

1692
01:48:57,145 --> 01:48:59,440
我必须问你一个非常私人的问题
I have to ask you a very personal question.

1693
01:48:59,441 --> 01:49:03,614
你跟前任德温特太太之间的感情很幸福吗
Were relations between you and the late Mrs.de Winter perfectly happy?

1694
01:49:05,286 --> 01:49:09,031
你跟前任德温特太太之间的感情很幸福吗
Were relations between you and the late Mrs.be Winter perfectly happy?

1695
01:49:09,042 --> 01:49:12,066
我不能再忍受了  你不妨现在就知道
I won’t stand this any longer! You might as well know now...

1696
01:49:12,296 --> 01:49:13,285
(GAVEL BANGING)

1697
01:49:14,469 --> 01:49:16,660
休庭直到午餐过后  德温特先生
CORONER:We’ll adjourn till after lunch.

1698
01:49:15,007 --> 01:49:18,625
Mr.de Winter,I presume you’ll be available for us then?

1699
01:49:16,660 --> 01:49:18,955
我相信那时你会为我们腾出时间来吧

1700
01:49:18,957 --> 01:49:21,720
我告诉过你该吃点早餐
I told you,you should have had some breakfast.

1701
01:49:21,888 --> 01:49:24,360
你只是饿了，没别的
You’re hungry. That’s what’s the matter with you.

1702
01:49:29,396 --> 01:49:31,438
弗里思先生说您也许想吃家里的午餐
Mr.Frith thought you might like to have some lunch from the house,

1703
01:49:31,606 --> 01:49:32,606
就让我带来了
and sent me with it.

1704
01:49:32,774 --> 01:49:34,400
不要紧，停在街角吧
No,that’s fine. Pull around the corner.

1705
01:49:34,568 --> 01:49:36,235
好的，先生
Very good,sir.

1706
01:49:46,039 --> 01:49:47,916
我真是太笨了  这样都会晕倒
Awfully foolish of me,fainting like that.

1707
01:49:47,968 --> 01:49:50,888
胡说  如果你没晕倒的话  我真的要发脾气了
Nonsense. If you hadn’t fainted like that,I’d have really lost my temper.

1708
01:49:50,888 --> 01:49:52,869
亲爱的  请小心点
Daring,please be careful.

1709
01:49:59,021 --> 01:50:01,106
亲爱的  在这儿等一会
Darling,wait here a few moments. I’ll see if I can old Frank.

1710
01:50:01,106 --> 01:50:03,818
-我去看看能否找到老弗兰克  -去吧  亲爱的
Of course,darling. Don’t worry about me.I’ll be all right.

1711
01:50:03,818 --> 01:50:07,884
-别担心我  我会没事的  -确定?  好的
Sure?

1712
01:50:07,884 --> 01:50:11,732
给  喝点这个  会舒服点的
Here,try a spot of this. Do you good.

1713
01:50:11,742 --> 01:50:13,723
谢谢
Thank you.

1714
01:50:15,704 --> 01:50:18,509
-你确定没事吗  -确定
-Are you all right? -Yes,of course.

1715
01:50:18,520 --> 01:50:20,918
-不会很久的  -行了
-I won’t be long. -Right you are.

1716
01:50:24,493 --> 01:50:25,653
Hello.

1717
01:50:26,027 --> 01:50:29,572
新娘子今天觉得如何呀
And how does the bride find herself today?

1718
01:50:31,971 --> 01:50:35,610
我是说  跟迈克西姆的婚姻并不如意吧
I say,marriage with Max is not exactly a bed of roses,is it?

1719
01:50:35,620 --> 01:50:38,018
我觉得你最好在迈克西姆回来之前离开
I think you’d better go before Maxim gets back.

1720
01:50:38,018 --> 01:50:41,147
他会吃醋?  我根本无权指责他
Oh,jealous,in he? Well,I can’t say I blame him.

1721
01:50:41,147 --> 01:50:43,962
但你不认为我是个大坏蛋  是吗
But you don’t think I’m the big bad wolf,do you?

1722
01:50:43,962 --> 01:50:47,090
我可不是  我是个非常平凡又和善可亲的人
I’m not,you know.I’m a perfectly ordinary,harmless bloke.

1723
01:50:47,090 --> 01:50:50,010
我觉得你对这件事处理的很好
And I think you’re behaving splendidly over all this. Perfectly splendidly.

1724
01:50:50,010 --> 01:50:51,991
非常的棒

1725
01:50:51,991 --> 01:50:54,597
自从上次见过你之后  你稍微变成熟了
You know,you’ve grown up a bit since I last saw you. It's no wonder...

1726
01:50:54,597 --> 01:50:56,891
-怪不得   -你想干吗  费弗尔
What do you want,Favell?

1727
01:50:56,891 --> 01:51:00,635
你好啊  迈克斯  你过得很好吧
Oh,hello,Max. Things are going pretty well for you,aren't they?

1728
01:51:00,645 --> 01:51:02,053
比你以前预期的更好
Better than you ever expected.

1729
01:51:02,053 --> 01:51:04,086
起初我还很担心你
I was rather worried about you at first. That's why I came down to the inquest.

1730
01:51:04,086 --> 01:51:06,589
所以我过来听审

1731
01:51:06,589 --> 01:51:08,799
我被你的关心所打动  但如果你不介意的话
Well,I'm touched by your solicitude.

1732
01:51:07,202 --> 01:51:09,818
But if you don't mind,we’d rather like to have our lunch.

1733
01:51:08,799 --> 01:51:10,228
我们想要用午餐了
Lunch? I say,what a jolly idea. Rather like a picnic,isn’t it?

1734
01:51:10,238 --> 01:51:14,305
午餐  多么好的主意啊  更像是野餐  不是吗

1735
01:51:14,305 --> 01:51:18,152
对不起  是否介意我把这个放在这儿
I’m so sorry. Do you mind if I put this there?

1736
01:51:18,163 --> 01:51:19,331
迈克斯  老兄
You know,Max,old boy,I really think I ought to talk things over with you.

1737
01:51:19,331 --> 01:51:22,115
我真的觉得我应该跟你商量点事

1738
01:51:22,125 --> 01:51:24,419
商量什么
Talk what things over?

1739
01:51:24,419 --> 01:51:27,130
首先  那些船板上的那些洞
Well,those holes in the planking,for one thing.

1740
01:51:27,130 --> 01:51:30,154
那些洞是从里面被凿开的
Those holes that were drilled from the inside.

1741
01:51:30,154 --> 01:51:32,656
-穆勒  -什么事  先生
-Oh,Mullen? -Yes,sir?

1742
01:51:32,656 --> 01:51:35,680
可以把我的车开去加油吗
Would you,like a good fellow,have my car filled with petrol?

1743
01:51:35,680 --> 01:51:37,661
-快没油了  -好的  先生
-It’s almost empty. -Very good,sir.

1744
01:51:37,661 --> 01:51:40,790
-还有  穆勒  把门关上吧  -是的  先生
-And,Mullen,close the door,will you? -Yes,sir.

1745
01:51:40,946 --> 01:51:43,448
烟熏到你了吗
Does this bother you?

1746
01:51:50,435 --> 01:51:52,624
老兄  我有种强烈的感觉
You know,old boy,I buys a strong feeling that before the day’s out,

1747
01:51:52,624 --> 01:51:55,231
不出一天  有些人将会
somebody’s going to make use of that rather expressive,

1748
01:51:55,335 --> 01:52:00,132
用婉转的方式表达一般所说的"谋杀"
though somewhat old-fashioned term,“foul play.”

1749
01:52:01,174 --> 01:52:04,198
你们觉得无聊吗
Am I boring you with all this?

1750
01:52:04,198 --> 01:52:07,848
没有吗  很好
No?

1751
01:52:07,952 --> 01:52:11,184
迈克斯  我发觉自己处于一个相当尴尬的立场
Good.Well,you see,Max,I find myself in a rather awkward position.

1752
01:52:11,184 --> 01:52:15,564
你只要看一下这封信就明白了  是丽贝卡写的
You’ve only got to read this note to understand.It’s from Rebecca.

1753
01:52:15,564 --> 01:52:18,692
还有  她真是有先见之明
And,what’s more,she had the foresight to put a date on it.

1754
01:52:18,692 --> 01:52:21,716
她去世的那天写给我的
She wrote me the day she died.

1755
01:52:21,716 --> 01:52:23,801
不巧地是  那天晚上我去参加派对了
Incidentally,I was at a party on that night

1756
01:52:23,801 --> 01:52:25,887
所以直到第二天我才看到
so I didn’t get it until the next day.

1757
01:52:25,991 --> 01:52:27,972
为什么你觉得我会对这封信感兴趣呢
And what makes you think that note would interest me?

1758
01:52:28,076 --> 01:52:30,475
我不会跟你讨论信的内容
Oh,I’m not gonna bother you with the contents now.

1759
01:52:30,475 --> 01:52:33,081
但我可以肯定那不是一个打算当晚
But I can assure you that it is not the note of a woman

1760
01:52:33,081 --> 01:52:36,210
自杀的女人会写的信
who intends to drown herself that same night.

1761
01:52:38,399 --> 01:52:41,527
顺便说一下  你怎么处理以前的骨骸
By the way,what do you do with old bones? Bury them?

1762
01:52:41,527 --> 01:52:44,134
葬了它们  还是怎样

1763
01:52:44,134 --> 01:52:47,366
然而  暂且
However,for the time being...

1764
01:52:47,366 --> 01:52:48,076
迈克斯
You know,Max,I’m getting fed up with my job as a motorcar salesman.

1765
01:52:48,076 --> 01:52:51,433
我真的受够了做汽车销售员的工作

1766
01:52:51,433 --> 01:52:53,831
我不知道你是否曾经经受过那种感觉
I don’t know if you’ve ever experienced the feeling

1767
01:52:53,831 --> 01:52:56,751
开着一辆价值不菲却不属于你的汽车
of driving an expensive motorcar which isn’t your own?

1768
01:52:56,751 --> 01:52:58,732
但那真的会气死人
But it can be very,very exasperating.

1769
01:52:58,732 --> 01:53:02,069
你知道我什么意思  你想拥有自己的车
You know what I mean. You want to own the car yourself.

1770
01:53:02,069 --> 01:53:05,197
我经常问自己  迁居到乡下会是什么样
I oftan wonder what it would be like to ratire to the country.

1771
01:53:05,197 --> 01:53:08,116
拥有一个有着几英亩猎场的漂亮的小地方
Have a nice little place with a few acres of shooting.

1772
01:53:08,116 --> 01:53:10,098
我从未弄明白那要花一年的时间
I’ve never figured out what it what it would cost a year,

1773
01:53:10,098 --> 01:53:12,079
但我想要跟你谈谈
but I’d like to talk about it with you.

1774
01:53:12,079 --> 01:53:13,486
我想听听你的建议
I’d like to have your advice on how to live comfortably without hard work.

1775
01:53:13,486 --> 01:53:15,520
怎样能不用努力工作而过着舒适的生活

1776
01:53:17,501 --> 01:53:20,420
你好  费弗尔  你找我吗  迈克西姆
Hello,Favell. You looking for me,Maxim?

1777
01:53:20,420 --> 01:53:25,738
是的  费弗尔先生跟我有点事要谈
Yes.

1778
01:53:22,713 --> 01:53:25,546
Mr.Favell and I have a little business transaction on hand.

1779
01:53:25,738 --> 01:53:28,658
我想我们最好去小酒馆解决
I think we had better conduct it over at the inn.

1780
01:53:28,658 --> 01:53:32,829
那儿也许有包间
They may have a private room there.

1781
01:53:32,829 --> 01:53:35,540
待会儿见
Well,see you later.

1782
01:53:35,540 --> 01:53:38,564
去找朱利安上校  告诉他我要马上见他
Find Colonel Julyan. Tell him I want to see him immediately.

1783
01:53:38,564 --> 01:53:41,066
走吧  费弗尔
Come on.Favell.Let’s go.

1784
01:53:45,758 --> 01:53:48,156
